{"_id":"0sXgmDnR9n2mtmb3","name":"Setting Rules","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Setting Rules</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p><cite>Savage Worlds</cite> range from dark and gritty detective tales to cinematic epics to political thrillers. These rules provide a great framework for anything you want to do, but adding the right Setting Rules really brings the world and the action to life!</p>\n<p><strong>When to Use These Rules:</strong> Setting Rules accommodate different play styles and help emulate genres or tropes of established settings—like those of a book or movie that’s inspired you. This lets you easily tweak the rules to make a gritty crime drama more bloody, or an adventurous space romp more fun—all without changing the core of the game.</p>\n<p><strong>The Basics:</strong> Each Setting Rule is different. Some apply during @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Character Creation Summary]{character creation} while others tweak @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Combat}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skills}, or even @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} use in some way.</p>\n<aside class=\"gray-slate\">\n<h2>Setting Rule Checklist</h2>\n<p>Use the following list to choose the Setting Rules for your game, coloring in the dots so everyone in the group knows which rules are in effect.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Born A Hero]{Born A Hero}:</strong> Player characters ignore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} requirements for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} during @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Character Creation Summary]{character creation}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Born from War]{Born from War}:</strong> Player characters start with a free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Background Edge} that must be tied to their backstory experiences during the Last War during @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Character Creation Summary]{character creation}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Conviction]{Conviction}:</strong> Heroes gain Conviction Tokens that can be used to add a d6 to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Traits} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage]{damage} rolls for one round. Conviction is awarded for triumph (overcoming a great obstacle important to that character), and tragedy (a personal setback, death of a friend or ally, etc). Conviction effects may be extended by spending a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Creative Combat]{Creative Combat}:</strong> A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} allows the character to roll on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Creative Combat]{special table} that grants additional effects.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dumb Luck]{Dumb Luck}:</strong> Characters may spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} after a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, allowing another chance for success in unusual and unexpected ways.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dynamic Backlash]{Dynamic Backlash}:</strong> A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane} skill roll forces the player to roll on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dynamic Backlash]{special table} with various chaotic results.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fanatics]{Fanatics}:</strong> Enemy thugs take the damage for their masters.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fast Healing]{Fast Healing}:</strong> Characters make natural @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{healing} rolls once per day instead of every five days, and recover a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bumps and Bruises]{Bumps &amp; Bruises} every four hours instead of every day.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heroes Never Die]{Heroes Never Die}:</strong> Heroes and named villains rarely actually die but return in some way after being defeated.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Glory and Infamy]{Glory and Infamy}:</strong> Glory or Infamy track the reputation of the Player Characters. As it increases they are awarded with benefits from those that respect the reputation of the character.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.More Skill Points]{More Skill Points}:</strong> Player characters in advanced or specialized settings start with 15 skill points.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.No Power Points]{No Power Points}:</strong> Those with arcane backgrounds don’t track @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} but instead subtract half the listed Power Point cost (round up) from their skill roll to activate the ability. Powers may be maintained as desired at a −1 penalty to all further arcane skill rolls.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Skill Specialization]{Skill Specialization}:</strong> Characters choose a specialization for each skill and subtract 2 when using other variations.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmored Hero]{Unarmored Hero}:</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} without armor add +2 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} rolls.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wound Cap]{Wound Cap}:</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} never suffer more than four @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{wounds} from a single hit.</li>\n</ul>\n</aside>\n<img src=\"modules/swade-core-rules/assets/art/pg142_quote_setting_rules.webp\" /></div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_s3sjll7e4a","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. The Adventure Toolkit","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-rules.vrgPhQvUqoH4LGcr"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":21},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"0tIqaAVU3wnwp11Q","name":"Evil Domain","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Evil Domain</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Aspects:</strong> Death, destruction, hate violence</li>\n<li><strong>Deities:</strong> The Dark Six, Some follows of Blood of Vol, Cults of the Dragon Below</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Augury]{Augury}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{Blast}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{Blind}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{Burst}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Champion of Faith]{Champion of Faith}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Curse]{Curse}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Damage Field]{Damage Field}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Darkness}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Consecrate/Desecrate Ground]{Desecrate Ground}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{Detect/Conceal Arcana}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Divination]{Divination}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Drain Power Points]{Drain Power Points}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{Entangle}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fear]{Fear}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Gift of Battle]{Gift of Battle}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Glyph]{Glyph}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{Havoc}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Intangibility]{Intangibility}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Planar Binding]{Planar Binding}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Planar Travel]{Planar Travel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{Puppet}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Resurrection]{Resurrection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sanctuary]{Sanctuary}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Secret Writing]{Secret Writing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Sloth/Speed}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{Slumber}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{Sound/Silence}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{Stun}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]