s.Thievery]{Thievery} without them.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Tinker's Tools]{Tinker's Tools}</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Warforged Repair Kit]{Warforged Repair Kit}</td>\n<td>25 gp</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Five uses.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"swadetest","system":"swade","coreVersion":"0.7.8","systemVersion":"0.15.0"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ib2qus6sn1","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/2.1. Gear Tables","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1}}}
{"_id":"5m5M4Xbo2onkFeL3","name":"Languages","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Languages</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>In Eberron, languages reflect culture and geography; a dwarf raised in Breland might not know Dwarvish, but a halfling raised in the Mror Holds might. The historical development of languages and cultures also explains the scripts used to write various languages. For example, the Orc language is written using the Goblin script, because the orcs of Khorvaire learned writing from the goblins. Common is the language of the Five Nations and the language of trade in Khorvaire, known by most of its people. Goblin was the trade language of the goblin empire of Dhakaan and survives as the primary language in Darguun, Droaam, and the Shadow Marches. Goblin displaced the Orc language; the people of the Shadow Marches typically speak Goblin, and Orc is an exotic language. Members of all races in Xen'drik speak Giant and use it as their trade language. Infernal is the common tongue of all fiends, while Celestial is \"the tongue of Siberys.\"</p>\n<h3>Welcome to Eberron</h3>\n<p>With the DM's approval, you can exchange a language granted by your race for a different language from the Standard Languages of Eberron table. Ifyour halfling was raised in the Mror Holds, you might replace Halfling with Dwarvish to reflect that background. The DM may change the languages assigned to a monster or NPC. An ogre from Droaam likely speaks Goblin instead of Giant.</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Standard Languages</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Language</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Typical Speakers</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Script</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Common</td>\n<td>Citizens of Khorvaire</td>\n<td>Common</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dwarven</td>\n<td>Mror Holds</td>\n<td>Dwarvish</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Elven</td>\n<td>Aerenal, Valenar</td>\n<td>Sylvan</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td>Goblin</td>\n<td>Darguun, Droaam, Shadow Marches, monsters of Khorvaire</td>\n<td>Goblin</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Gnomish</td>\n<td>Zilargo</td>\n<td>Dwarvish</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Halfling</td>\n<td>Talenta Plains</td>\n<td>Goblin</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Exotic Languages</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Language</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Typical Speakers</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Script</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Argon</td>\n<td>Barbarians of Argonnessen and Seren</td>\n<td>Common</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Draconic</td>\n<td>Kobolds, lizardfolk, troglodytes, dragons, arcane uses</td>\n<td>Draconic</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Druidic</td>\n<td>Druids, Eldeen Reaches</td>\n<td>Draconic</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Giant</td>\n<td>Native inhabitants of Xen'drik</td>\n<td>Giant</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Orc</td>\n<td>Isolated orc tribes</td>\n<td>Goblin</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Riedran</td>\n<td>People of Sarlona</td>\n<td>Common</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Sahuagin</td>\n<td>Sahuagin, sailors</td>\n<td>Sahuagin</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Khyber's Tongue</td>\n<td>Denizens of Khyber, symbionts</td>\n<td>Daelkyr</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Planar Languages</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Language</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Typical Speakers</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Script</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Celestial</td>\n<td>Celestials, Archons of Shavarath, couatl, shulassukar</td>\n<td>Celestial</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Daan</td>\n<td>lawful outsiders of Daanvi</td>\n<td>Daan</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Infernal</td>\n<td>Beings of Shavarath, Lords of Dust, tieflings</td>\n<td>Infernal</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Irial</td>\n<td>Deathless, energy beings of Irian</td>\n<td>Celestial</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Kythric</td>\n<td>Slaadi, choatic outsiders of Kythri</td>\n<td>Daan</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Quori</td>\n<td>Inspired, kalashtar, quori</td>\n<td>Quori</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Primordial</td>\n<td>Elementals</td>\n<td>Primordial</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Sylvan</td>\n<td>Dryads, eladrin, fey of Thelanis and woodland beings</td>\n<td>Sylvan</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_intbwo9s2if","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"5rMnHhd79ES5Ddy7","name":"Powers Summary List","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"header\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p>Powers Sumamry List</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<h2 class=\"toc-links-title\">Magic and Powers</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Activation]{Activation}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Arcane Backgrounds}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Powers Summary List]{Powers Summary list}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cantrips]{Cantrips}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Schools of Magic}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trappings}</h3>\n</div>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3> </h3>\n</div>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Powers</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Power</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" style=\"width:5%\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" style=\"width:5%\">Power<br />Points</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" style=\"width:5%\">Range</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" style=\"width:5%\">Dur</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" style=\"width:5%\">School</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Accelerate Healing]{Accelerate Healing}</td>\n<td>V</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>T</td>\n<td>24H</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Target makes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{natural healing} every 24 hours, with +2 on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Analyze Foe]{Analyze Foe}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Sm x2</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Div}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Opposed Roll} vs @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} for +1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} rolls effecting target and −1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} rolls effecting caster. +2 and −2 on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Animate War Tree]{Animate War Tree}</td>\n<td>H</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>T</td>\n<td>10m</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Awakens a tree as a war tree. It is a wild card on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abj}</td>\n<td>Enemy casters subtract 2 (4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) when targeting this character; reduces @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage]{damage} a like amount.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Augury]{Augury}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Self</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Div}</td>\n<td>Recieve an omen about a specific course of action.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Baleful Polymorph]{Baleful Polymorph}</td>\n<td>V</td>\n<td>3+</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Trans}</td>\n<td>l from Size–2 to Size 3 is transformed into a relatively harmless creature.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}</td>\n<td>V</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Anj}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Opposed Roll} vs @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} to <em>banish</em> entities.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Creates 5\" (10 yards) long, 1\" (2 yards) tall, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} 10 barrier.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Battle Song]{Battle Song}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>MBT</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enc}</td>\n<td>Grants @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} to creatures within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{Beast Friend}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Special</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>10m</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enc}</td>\n<td>Controls animals.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{Blast}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Sm x2</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evo}</td>\n<td>2d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-