rmor} +2 on success, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} +2 on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{Puppet}</td>\n<td>V</td>\n<td>–1</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>1m/R</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enc}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Opposed Roll} vs @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}to control target.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{Relief}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I/1h</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Removes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}; &amp; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stun} with raise.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{Repair}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>T</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Restores @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} to constructs and objects.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Resurrection]{Resurrection}</td>\n<td>H</td>\n<td>20</td>\n<td>T</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Brings the dead back to life.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sanctuary]{Sanctuary}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>T</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enc}</td>\n<td>Foes must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to attack.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{Scrying}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Self</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Div}</td>\n<td>Caster can see and hear a target and surrounding area remotely.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Secret Writing]{Secret Writing}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>T</td>\n<td>Perm</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Ill}</td>\n<td>Disguise the contents of a written message.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{Sentry}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Sm x2</td>\n<td>Special</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abj}</td>\n<td>Creates a sentry to watch over an area or object.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Shape Change]{Shape Change}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Special</td>\n<td>Self</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Trans}</td>\n<td>Caster takes on the form of various beings.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Sloth/Speed}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I/5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Trans}</td>\n<td>Increases or decreases @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Movement}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{Slumber}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>1h</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enc}</td>\n<td>Puts victims to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Sleep]{Sleep}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Trans}</td>\n<td>Increase a weapon’s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage]{damage} by +2/+4.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{Sound/Silence}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Sm x5/Sm</td>\n<td>I/5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Ill}</td>\n<td>Create or mute sound.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{Speak Language}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>10m</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Div}</td>\n<td>Caster can speak and understand languages.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{Stun}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evo}</td>\n<td>Target is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{Summon Ally}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Special</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Conjures an ally of various sorts.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{Summon Beast}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Special</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Conjures mundane animals under characters control.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{Telekinesis}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>Sm x2</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Trans}</td>\n<td>Moves items with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} of d10 (d12 with a raise).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{Teleport}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Character teleports up to Smarts x5 miles distant.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Time Stop]{Time Stop}</td>\n<td>H</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Trans}</td>\n<td>Caster takes an additional turn (of 4 actions with a raise).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{Wall Walker}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Trans}</td>\n<td>Character can walk on walls at half @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} (full Pace with raise).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{Warrior's Gift}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Con}</td>\n<td>Grant target a Combat @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edge}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wish]{Wish}</td>\n<td>L</td>\n<td>20</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Uni}</td>\n<td>Choose one of several reality-altering events.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Zombie]{Zombie}</td>\n<td>V</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>1h</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Nec}</td>\n<td>Raises and controls the undead.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3> </h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0re3y8nenvi","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.1. Using Magic","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":3}}}
