{"_id":"65n5URr0MER6n0yM","name":"Kalashtar","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Kalashtar</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>The kalashtar are a compound people, created from the union ofhumanity and renegade spirits from the plane of dreams-spirits called quori. Kalashtar are often seen as wise, spiritual people with great compassion for others. There is an unmistakable alien quality to the kalashtar, though, as they are haunted by the conflicts of their otherworldly spirits.</p>\n<h3>Bound to Spirits</h3>\n<p>Every kalashtar has a connection to a spirit of light, a bond shared by other members of their bloodline. Kalashtar appear human, but their spiritual connection affects them in a variety of ways. Kalashtar have symmetrical, slightly angular features, and their eyes often glow when they are focused or expressing strong emotions. Kalashtar can't directly communicate with their quori spirits. Rather, they might experience this relationship as a sense of instinct and inspiration, drawing on the memories of the spirit when they dream. This connection grants kalashtar minor psionic abilities, as well as protection from psychic attacks. All of these quori dream-spirits are virtuous, but some are warriors and others are more contemplative. Work together with the DM to determine the nature ofyour linked spirit. Typically, a kalashtar knows the name and nature of their spirit, but some may know nothing of their spirit or the source of their psychic gifts, such as an orphan kalashtar raised among strangers.</p>\n<h3>Hunted by Nightmares</h3>\n<p>The virtuous spirits tied to the kalashtar fled from the dream-realm of Dal Quor to escape evil spirits that dominate it. The rebel quori believe that through meditation and devotion, they can change the fundamental nature of Dal Quor, shifting the balance from darkness to light. Most kalashtar communities focus on acts of devotion known as the Path of Light. But the dark powers of Dal Quor have their own plans for Eberron. Through the force known as the Dreaming Dark, these monsters manipulate the folk of Khorvaire to eliminate kalashtar whenever possible.</p>\n<p>Many kalashtar defend themselves from the Dreaming Dark by focusing on devotion to the Path of Light. Others, though, seek out the agents of the Dreaming Dark and oppose their plans, or protect the innocent however they can. Still other kalashtar grow up isolated, knowing nothing about Dal Quor or the Dreaming Dark. Such orphans might use their abilities for personal gain or otherwise act against the virtuous instincts of their quori spirits; this can cause internal conflicts and violent mood swings.</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Dual Mind: </strong>Because of the guidance from the quori spirit with which they are bonded, kalashtar begin play with a d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} instead of a d4. This increases their maximum @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} to d12+1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Language}:</strong> Kalashtar start with a d8 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Quori} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Riedran} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Common}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Hunted]{Hunted (Major)}: </strong>Kalashtar are constantly hunted by the Dreaming Dark and the Inspired of Reidra.</li>\n<li><strong>Mental Discipline:</strong> With their connection with their Quori, kalashtar are incredibly disciplined mentally. They recieve a +1 bonus to all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Psionics]{Psionics} rolls.</li>\n<li><strong>Mind Link: </strong>Kalashtar have the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Psionics)]{Arcane Background (Psionics)} Edge and begin with the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Link]{mind link}</em> power as one of their known powers granted by the Edge.</li>\n<li><strong>Naturally Psionic: </strong>Kalashtar begins play with a d4 in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Psionics]{Psionics} skill. This increases their maximum @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Psionics]{Psionics} to d12+1.​</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/kalashtar.webp\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/kalashtar.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.eOQLfdMRa4e43zbF"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_di56kj2145l","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"68yLEak0FiDyj8Da","name":"Nautical Campaigns","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Nautical Campaigns</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>The following chapter contains tools the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Game Mastering]{Dungeon Master} can use for nautical based campaigns, such as:</p>\n<h2>Navigation and Combat</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Navigation]{NAVIGATION}:</strong> How to navigate the seas from hex to hex.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{NAUTICAL CONTACT}:</strong> Once contact is established, manuevering to catch a ship prior to using the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases} rules.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor and Swimming]{ARMOR AND SWIMMING}:</strong> Rules for swimming in armor.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fighting Below Deck]{FIGHTING BELOW DECKS}:</strong> Fighting in the cramped quarters below decks on a ship.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Repairs]{SHIP REPAIRS}:</strong> The means to repair a ship of any wounds that it sustains.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<h2>Crew Upkeep</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Pay]{CREW PAY}:</strong> Expected pay rate for sailors.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Provisions]{CREW PROVISIONS}:</strong> How much food is needed for a crew.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cabin Fever]{CABIN FEVER}:</strong> Effects of long sea voyages.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Carouse]{CAROUSE}:</strong> How the crew can recver from Cabin Fever.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<h2>Hazards</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Careening]{CAREENING}:</strong> Maintenance needed on a ship at sea.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Fire]{SHIP FIRE}:</strong> Fire is one of the greatest dangers aboard a ship.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Storms at Sea]{STORMS AT SEA}:</strong> How to navigate through a storm at sea.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":17},"cf":{"id":"temp_s3sjll7e4a","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. The Adventure Toolkit","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"6mCmMYXFOfFkLUHJ","name":"Gear","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"header\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p>Gear</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>This section contains rules and equipment.</p>\n<h2>Costs</h2>\n<p>Characters are assumed to have clothes and other personal items. If the DM allows it, adventurers may also have a home with other supplies and necessities. </p>\n<p>The starting funds (300 gp) are for “adventuring gear” in addition to such personal items. The costs listed on the following pages represent standards; in the marketplace or the bazaar, all costs are negotiable. Character gear lists don’t need to include anything beyond “adventuring gear”.</p>\n<p>Use the lists and prices in this book as a baseline for your game when looking for equipment that isn't listed here.</p>\n<p>Some items are extremely difficult to price because they're created by decree or necessity, such as engineers and soldiers in a siege building catapults and trebuchets. Their prices reflect an estimate of the time and resources needed to create them.  </p>\n<h2>Gear Tables</h2>\n<p>Use the following links to view consolidated tables of available gear and equipment.</p>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Common Gear Table]{Common Gear}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor Table]{Armor}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shields Table]{Shields}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Melee Weapons Table]{Melee Weapons}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ranged Weapons Table]{Ranged Weapons}</h3>\n</div>\n<h2>Special Weapons</h2>\n<p>Use the following links to view consolidated tables of available special weapons.</p>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Alchemical Items Table]{Alchemical Items}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Seige Engines Table]{Seige Engines}</h3>\n</div>\n<h2>Materials and Craftsmanship</h2>\n<p>Weapons and armor in particular are often created with special materials or from very fine craftsmanship.</p>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Masterwork]{Masterwork}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Special Materials]{Special Materials}</h3>\n</div>\n<h2>Gear Notes</h2>\n<p>Read the notes below before you go to the outfitters to understand what various keywords mean.</p>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{Armor Piercing (AP)}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage]{Damage}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy Weapon (HW)}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Minimum Strength]{Minimum Strength}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Rate of Fire]{Rate of Fire}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reload]{Reload}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{Two Hands}</h3>\n</div>\n<h2>Encumbrance</h2>\n<p>Most of the time you don’t need to worry about how much weight a character is carrying. If it becomes important to track, use the <strong>Encumbrance Levels</strong> table below. If a character carries more than the listed weight, he’s Encumbered.</p>\n<p>Encumbered characters subtract 2 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} (minimum 1″), running rolls, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and all linked skills, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls made to resist <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}</strong>.</p>\n<p>At three times the lifted weight or more, he can move at a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} of 1 for a number of rounds equal to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor}. Every round thereafter he must succeed at a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll or take a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}.</p>\n<p>The maximum weight a character can lift or carry is four times the listed weight.</p>\n<table class=\"table list-table\" style=\"width:33%\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Encumbrance</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Strength</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Can carry weight up to...</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>20 lbs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>40 lbs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>60 lbs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>80 lbs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>100 lbs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Each +1</td>\n<td>+20 lbs</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Bulky Items: </strong>Carrying a bulky, awkward, or unbalanced item, such as a large box, treasure chest, a person, and so on, may make a character Encumbered despite its actual weight (DM’s call).</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_7e7xz1a6a2k","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":4}}}
{"_id":"6us72CBRKlXvcq70","name":"Draconic Bloodline","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Draconic</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>There’s a dragon lurking somewhere in the family tree. Its scion gains claws (Str+d4), and scaly skin (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor} +1).</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>★ Advanced Form: </strong>The sorcerer’s claws are now AP 2 and he gains @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Enviromental Resistance]{enviromental resistance} common to her ancestry (acid for black, fire for red, etc.).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_w2j6cd7pbcs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.4. Bloodlines","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"6x2wz5HTaHOr1fy4","name":"Familiars","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Familiars</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>“Familiars” are small creatures (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} −2 or −3) that serve as a loyal pets and magical companions to certain kinds of spellcasters.</p>\n<p>Familiars are loyal to their masters but aren’t slaves. They are typical but very smart versions of their species and can occasionally be distracted by their own inherent instincts. For example, a cat might interrupt its task to chase a mouse or take a brief nap, and a dog will almost certainly bark when a stranger approaches.</p>\n<p>A familiar is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card} with respect to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} and rolling a Wild Die with its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} rolls. It doesn’t get @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies}, but the mage can spend his own on its behalf. The familiar can understand its master’s speech and vice-versa (others hear only the creature’s natural sounds), though concepts are limited to what a member of its species might understand.</p>\n<p>The familiar has 5 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} of its own. It cannot cast spells, but the mage can draw on them as if they were his own. They recharge separately and at the same rate as the mage’s.</p>\n<p>The bond between the familiar and the mage makes it immune to the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{beast friend}</em> power.</p>\n<p>If a familiar dies, the hero is automatically @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned} (no matter how far away he is). He can summon another after 10 days and can change the type if she chooses.</p>\n<p>Familiars don’t advance, but instead gain one of the advantages below for each of its master’s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Ranks} (including @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice}) and for every fourth advance the hero gains past @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Legendary}.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The owner may use the familiar’s senses as if they were her own, with a maximum range of 10 miles. She is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted and Vulnerable} while doing so.</li>\n<li>The mage can increase one of the familiar’s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Traits} one die type (no more than once per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait}).</li>\n<li>The familiar gains an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edge}. It must make sense for the familiar’s species (DM’s call) and meet the Requirements as usual.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ogabsqlqv6a","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Magic","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1}}}
{"_id":"7vlY8JDlvPt6Lju1","name":"Born from War","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<h2>Born from War</h2>\n<p>Every character starts with one free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Class Edge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Background Edge} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Professional Edge}. This edge must be tied to the story of your characters experiences during her life in the Last War.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_lfqse89fhyg","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Setting Rules","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-rules.JFQcPWutEKTvsjbn"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":2},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"7zqbhbtnoWaX6zHx","name":"Purchasing Magic Items","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Purchasing Magic Items</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Most towns have an apothecary shop with a few potions for sale, a few local merchants reselling magical items, or even individuals looking to sell of devices they no longer need.</p>\n<p>When the adventurers want to buy magic items, roll on the table below to see what's available that week (or month if it's a particularly isolated or low-magic area).</p>\n<p>The table has three entries:</p>\n<p><strong>Potions &amp; Scrolls:</strong> Half the items are potions and half are scrolls, rounding in favor of potions. Roll randomly from the tables on the following pages.</p>\n<p><strong>Healing:</strong> This tells you how many potions of minor healing, ubiquitous across Khorvaire, are available from various vendors. This is in addition to any healing offered by local House Jorasco or healers (prices for a healer's services are equivalent to potions of healing).</p>\n<p><strong>Other Items:</strong> This tells you how many other magical treasures may be found or purchased in the settlement. If the result is positive, roll on the Other Item table to determine the category, then roll on the appropriate subtable. If the category is a Wondrous Item, the GM chooses which item is available.</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Magic Items Availability</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Settlement</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Potions &amp; Scrolls</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Healing Potions</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Other Items</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Village</td>\n<td>d6−2</td>\n<td>1d4</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">d4−2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Town</td>\n<td>d6−1</td>\n<td>1d4+1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">d6−2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>City</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>1d6</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">d6−1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Large City</td>\n<td>d6+1</td>\n<td>1d6+1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">d6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Metropolis</td>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">d10</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Other Items Categories</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">d20</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Type</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1–3</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Armor</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4–7</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Shields</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8–11</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Weapons</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>12–13</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Rings</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>14–15</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Rods</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>16</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Staves</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>17–18</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Wands</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>19–20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center\">Wondrous Items</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>PURCHASING ITEMS</h2>\n<p>Exactly where the items are available is up to the Game Master. Common or relatively inexpensive items might be for sale at a shop on main straight. Rare or expensive items might require finding an elusive seller or completing some task in addition to the cost in gold.</p>\n<h2>EXOTIC ITEMS</h2>\n<p>A hero might seek out a specific magic item rather than waiting for it to appear at random. In that case, the character can either commission the item with a down payment (usually half its total cost in gold pieces), or perform a task or quest of some sort. At the Game Master's discretion, finding someone to make or sell such items might be an adventure on its own, or a Networking roll with a penalty determined by the item and the size of the settlement.</p>\n<h2 class=\"blue-example\">EXAMPLE: SHOPPING IN SANDPOINT</h2>\n<p>The party is about to set off on a quest to defeat an orc warlord. They decide to stock up on potions and other magical items before entering the warlord's domain.</p>\n<p>The adventurers are in a town, so the GM rolls on the Potions &amp; Scrolls column and determines there are three potions and two scrolls. She rolls randomly on the potions and scrolls tables to see which specific brews are available.</p>\n<p>Next she rolls for Healing Potions and gets a total of 3. The party scoops up all of them. Then she rolls on the Other Items column and gets a 2. She rolls a d20 twice and gets a ring and a rod.</p>\n<p>The Ring table gives her a ring of minor protection. She decides it's for sale at a secondhand merchant shop in town.</p>\n<p>The Rods table results in a rod of rulership. That's a fairly rare item, so the GM tells the group it's owned by a retired mage who will only sell it for a favor. They travel to the mage, who agrees to sell the rod at half value if the party will chase away a dangerous group of bugbears that have moved into her favorite herb-gathering spot.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-links-title\">Articles on Magic Items</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic Items]{Using Magic Items}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Purchasing Magic Items]{Purchasing Magic Items}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Enchantments]{Enchantments}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crafting Magic Items]{Crafting Magic Items}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},