{"_id":"8UH8HC3QNJ07Lt1u","name":"Elf, Drow","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Drow Elf</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Long ago on the continent of Xen'drik, the first drow fought beside the giants against the other elves. Tens of thousands of years have passed, and drow and other elves remember each other only as figures in their legends. The Undying Court and the patron ancestors of the Tairnadal remember the drow, but they have little occasion to teach their living descendants about these shadows of the distant past.</p>\n<p>When the elves fled to Aerenal, the drow remained on Xen'drik as subjects of the giants, and they were caught in the collapse of giant civilization. Today they linger on Xen'drik and have set their own course, free of the giants' malevolent influence.</p>\n<p>Three distinct drow cultures formed after the fall of the giants. The most numerous are the Vulkoori, hunters dedicated to a scorpion god called Vulkoor. They hunt giants and other dangers in their lands. Led by powerful druids and wizards, the Sulatar cling to traditions of elemental shaping that date back to the Age of Giants. They live in a handful of obsidian cities across Xen'drik, and believe that they are destined to cleanse the world in a fiery apocalypse. Finally, the Umbragen are descended from drow who fled into the depths of the earth when the giant civilization fell. They wield sophisticated magic in their unceasing battles against the daelkyr and the other aberrations of the underworld.</p>\n<h3>A Drow Adventurer</h3>\n<p>When creating a drow character, think about how you came to Khorvaire. Are you a Vulkoori hunter who accompanied an expedition home to Khorvaire, now seeking your way in this strange new world? Are you an Umbragen seeking powers that can help your people in their endless war? Or are you a Sulatar pursuing a personal path to glory?</p>\n<p>How do you react to meeting members of other elven cultures during your journeys? You might quickly recognize that most bear little resemblance to the terrors described in your people's legends, or you might have an almost instinctive reaction of distrust. You might have overcome your initial prejudices by the time the campaign begins, or perhaps you're working to build trust with another elf member ofyour adventuring party.</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Agile:</strong> Drow are graceful and agile. They start with a d6 in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} instead of a d4. This increases maximum @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} to d12+1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Drow Magic]{Drow Magic}:</strong> Drow have some innate magical abilities. The can cast @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cantrips]{cantrips} as if they knew each of the following powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{Beast friend}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fly]{fly}</em> and<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{light/darkness}</em> using their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} (or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} if they have one). They have 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} for activating these cantrips, regained as usual. Drow with an Arcane Background or Mystic Power add their bonus @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} to their pool but must still learn the spells if they wish to cast them normally.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Drow Magical Nature]{Drow Magical Nature}:</strong> Drow were born of ancient giant magic and have an inherent connection to arcane energies. Drow get a free reroll when rolling to resist enemy powers.</li>\n<li><strong>Keen Senses:</strong> Drow have exceptionally keen senses. They add +1 to any @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} check.</li>\n<li><strong>Intelligence:</strong> Draw are highly intelligent and long-lived. They start with a d6 in Smarts instead of a d4. This increases maximum Smarts to d12 + 1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Languages}: </strong>Drow start with a d8 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Elvish} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Common}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}:</strong> Drow eyes amplify light like a cat's, allowing them to see in the dark. Low Light Vision ignores up –2 penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness} remains unaffected.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Outsider (Drow)]{Outsider (Minor)}:</strong> Drow are seen as strange and exotic, a looked at differently that other elves. They have a −2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} as other races distrust them.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Slender (Drow)]{Slender}: </strong>Drow are graceful but more frail than other races. Their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} is reduced by 1 and they have a −1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} checks.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Warriors of the Wild]{Warriors of the Wild}:</strong> Drow are expert hunters, trackers and warriors. They recieve a +1  bonus to one of the following skills: @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival}.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/drow-elf.webp\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/drow-elf.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.v4IlpOHb2Raw0V33"},"cf":{"id":"temp_di56kj2145l","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"8VSzUH4Gypbxk1h5","name":"Arcane Background (Magic)","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<h2>Arcane Background (Magic)</h2>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Edge:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Magic)]{Arcane Background (Magic)}</li>\n<li><strong>Requirements:</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice}</li>\n<li><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts})</li>\n<li><strong>Backlash: </strong>When a wizard rolls a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} roll, the Dungeon Master rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Dynamic Backlash]{Dynamic Backlash} to see what happens.</li>\n<li><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>3</li>\n<li><strong>Power Points:</strong> 10</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Analyze Foe]{Analyze Foe}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Augury]{Augury}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{Beast Friend}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{Blast}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{Blind}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burrow]{Burrow}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{Burst}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{Conjure Item}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Curse]{Curse}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Damage Field]{Damage Field}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{Detect/Conceal Arcana}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Divination]{Divination}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Drain Power Points]{Drain Power Points}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{Elemental Manipulation}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{Empathy}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{Entangle}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Environmental Protection]{Environmental Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{Farsight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fear]{Fear}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fly]{Fly}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Gift of Battle]{Gift of Battle}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Glyph]{Glyph}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Grave Speak]{Grave Speak}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Growth/Shrink]{Growth/Shrink}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{Havoc}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{Illusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Intangibility]{Intangibility}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{Invisibility}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Leaping]{Leaping}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Light/Darkness}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{Locate}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{Lock/Unlock}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Magic Mark]{Magic Mark}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message]{Message}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Link]{Mind Link}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Reading]{Mind Reading}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Wipe]{Mind Wipe}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Object Reading]{Object Reading}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Planar Binding]{Planar Binding}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Planar Travel]{Planar Travel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{Puppet}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{Relief}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{Repair}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{Scrying}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Secret Writing]{Secret Writing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{Sentry}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Shape Change]{Shape Change}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Sloth/Speed}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{Slumber}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{Sound/Silence}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{Speak Language}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{Stun}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{Summon Ally}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{Summon Beast}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{Telekinesis}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{Teleport}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Time Stop]{Time Stop}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{Wall Walker}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{Warrior's Gift}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wish]{Wish}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Zombie]{Zombie}</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<h2>Arcane Magic</h2>\n<p>Arcane magic is a form of science. There are predictable rules that shape reality, and with proper study and force of will, anyone could potentially perform arcane magic. This is what makes arcane magic the foundation of civilization in the Five Nations: it can be taught, and once learned, it is entirely reliable. Arcane magic involves channeling ambient magical energy—the powers of the planes, the emanations of the Ring of Siberys—and focusing it to alter reality. The components of a spell—like verbal incantations, somatic gestures, and focus items—help this process, but the most important element of spellcasting is mental focus. Though a fighter could perfectly duplicate the words and gestures of a wizard, nothing would happen. You must cast the spell in your mind, harnessing and shaping mystical energy, and this can dangerous and exhausting.</p>\n<p>Spellcasting using Smarts is grounded in knowledge and logic. For these characters, casting a spell is like solving an equation—harnessing and carefully channeling the precise quantity of mystical energy required to produce the effect you’re looking for. A wizard may use words of power and mystic gestures to generate power, while an artificer instead relies on tools. But either way, you fundamentally know what you’re doing, which is why both artificers and wizards can prepare new spells each day. Arcane magic is a science, and you’re a scientist.</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Principles of Arcane Science]{Principles of Arcane Science}</h3>\n<p>Arcane magic involves the manipulation of vast, ambient mystical energies that permeate Eberron. These forces are largely omnipresent and invisible, not unlike gravity; they’re fundamental elements of the world, and in the course of time most cultures find some way to harness and manipulate them. Like most forms of science, there are different theories about how this science works, and specifically what force is being manipulated.</p>\n<p>You should consider what school of Arcane Science your wizard comers from and let that influence the kind of casting that your wizard accomplishes.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Principles of Arcane Science]{Siberyan Theory}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Principles of Arcane Science]{Externalist}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Principles of Arcane Science]{Sympathetic Magic}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Principles of Arcane Science]{Dominion Theory}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Principles of Arcane Science]{Fringe Traditions}</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Casting</h2>\n<p>Mages must make gestures with at least one free hand and speak aloud various magical words at least at a whisper. If either their hands are bound or they are prevented from speaking, they cannot cast their spells.</p>\n<h2>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trappings}</h2>\n<p>Mages are some of the most versatile casters in Eberron. There are no limitations on the kinds of trappings that can be utilized by a mage.</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yqngxv6403a","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.3. Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":3}}}
{"_id":"8WFdJqF66Mur1WvO","name":"Curse of Lycanthropy","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Curse of Lycanthropy</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Often called a curse, lycanthropy is an infectious disease. Anyone Wounded by a naturally-born lycanthrope must succeed at a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll or contract the disease</p>\n<p>A creature that catches lycanthropy displays no immediate symptoms The infected doesn't gain any of the profile's abilities until the night of the next full moon when the victim involuntarily assumes animal form and forgets his or her own identity.</p>\n<p>The character remains in animal form until the next dawn. He remembers nothing about the entire episode (or subsequent episodes) unless he succeeds with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll at –2, in which case he becomes aware of his condition.</p>\n<p>Success with the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> power and <strong>Neutralize Disease</strong> modifier cures the affliction if applied within the first hour after being infected. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the power cures the disease within the first full 24 hours.</p>\n<p>Consuming a potion of wolfsbane, created with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} roll at –2, within an hour of being infected gives an afflicted lycanthrope an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} check to recover from the disease.</p>\n<h2>Becoming a Lycanthrope</h2>\n<p>When a character becomes a lycanthrope, he develops the ability to change into multiple forms (listed with each type).</p>\n<p>Each form also has the following Special Abilities:</p>\n<p><strong>Change Shape:</strong> As a limited action, a lycanthrope can assume one of three forms: animal, hybrid, or original.</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Animal Form:</strong> Use the dire creature profile.</li>\n<li><strong><strong>Hybrid Form:</strong> </strong>Use the original profile with the following adjustments:\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Attributes:</strong> Increase these attributes by one die type—Spirit, Strength, and Vigor.</li>\n<li><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></li>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Armor]{Armor} +2:</strong> Thick hide.</li>\n<li><strong>Bite/Claw:</strong> Str+d6.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Enviromental Weakness]{Enviromental Weakness}:</strong> Silver</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Regeneration]{Fast Regeneration}:</strong> Lycanthropes may attempt a natural healing roll every round unless the Wounds were caused by silvered objects.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}:</strong> Lycanthropes ignore penalties for Dim and Dark Illumination.</li>\n<li><strong>Size +1:</strong> They hybrid form is one Size larger than the original</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Original:</strong> Use the original creature's profile with the Shape Change ability.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_5dvssh1comq","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Magic#/CF_SEP/1.4 Bestiary","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"98ANLmDp6UA6in6Q","name":"Chaos Domain","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Chaos Domain</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Aspects:</strong> Chaos, corruption, change, evil, disease, darkness</li>\n<li><strong>Deities:</strong> The Keeper, The Mockery, The Shadow, The Traveler, Cults of the Dragon Below</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Battle Song]{Battle Song}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{Blast}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{Blind}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{Burst}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Curse]{Curse}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Damage Field]{Damage Field}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Darkness}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Consecrate/Desecrate Ground]{Desecrate Ground}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-po