{"_id":"BsmS4It9vSMq0KRw","name":"Damaging","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<h3>Weapon Enchantment</h3>\n<p>The weapon’s damage increases by +1</p>\n<p><strong>Enchantment Points:</strong> 1</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 3,000 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</em></p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_d6wak2736pv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/6.1. Enchantments","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"C4LPZJYJ17isZfJD","name":"High Altitude","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<h2>High Altitude</h2>\n<p>Traversing landscapes at high elevations can cause @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}—and potentially worse—to those who aren’t used to it.</p>\n<p>When traveling at altitudes roughly a mile high or higher, a character must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll every four hours. Failure means the hero incurs a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} level. The roll is at −2 for elevation greater than 10,000 feet, and −4 (maximum) for higher than 15,000 feet.</p>\n<p>At the DM’s discretion, characters who are already acclimated to these elevations don’t need to roll</p>\n<p><strong>Death:</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated} victims die after [[/r 2d6]] hours.</p>\n<p><strong>Recovery:</strong> Victims one level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} per hour after resting for at least two full hours.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_5qurmfm60sv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Hazards","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-rules.kTqDlMHJo5qAda2v"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":5},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"Chvdt2b5TVbrkveK","name":"Energy Resistance","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<h3>Armor or Shield Enchantment</h3>\n<p>Grants environmental resistance against a single energy type, determined at creation, to a piece of armor or a shield. Damage from that source is reduced by 4 when the armor is worn, and the hero adds +4 when resisting any effect tied to that element.</p>\n<p>A leather jerkin of energy resistance (Cold), for example, helps its wearer avoid @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} from exposure (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hazards]{Hazards} on page 153) and damage from any attack with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trapping} of cold, ice, frost, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Enchantment Points:</strong> 1</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 2,000 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Enviromental Protection]{Enviromental protection}</em></p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_d6wak2736pv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/6.1. Enchantments","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"CzDdVjqGErM01jOV","name":"Fey Bloodline","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Fey</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>The capricious nature of the fey runs in this sorcerer’s family. She ignores @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Difficult Terrain} in the wilderness and has the “laughing touch.” If she successfully touches a target with her hands (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Touch Attack]{Touch Attacks}, page 142), the target is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}.</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>★ Advanced Form: </strong>Victims of a fey’s spell with a lingering effect, such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{blind}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{lower Trait}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{stun}</em>, and the like, subtract 2 from any roll made to recover.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_w2j6cd7pbcs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.4. Bloodlines","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
