{"_id":"KSBHDrReNupapVpQ","name":"Using Magic Items","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Using Magic Items</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Savage Eberron is a mythic place. Magic, both light and dark, flows through everything. The study and use of it has happpened by mystical beings such as dragons and Overlords, since the birth of the World ro present times. Much of this study and use has gone into pooling the energy into items of power.</p>\n<h3>Detecting Magic Items</h3>\n<p>In the magically-charged world of Eberron, any character with an Arcane Background can sense magical or divine auras within 5” (10 yards), unless they are magically concealed. This is an action.</p>\n<p>Detecting magic at a greater range or gaining specific information requires the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana} spell, which can also be used to reveal items or beings protected by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{conceal magic}. </p>\n<h3>Identifying Powers of Magical Items</h3>\n<p>There are three methods for determining what powers reside within an item. First, an arcane spellcaster can deduce the powers within an item simply through study. How long it takes is up to you, but a few minutes for a potion (given some basic testing equipment or a more dangerous taste test) and an hour for other items is usually enough.</p>\n<p>Second, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{Identify (from detect arcana)}</em> can be used to identify a magic item's powers and how they work.</p>\n<p>Third, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Object Reading]{object reading}</em> will reveal the powers of any object the spellcaster is touching when he casts the spell. This would be seperate from the casting to determine if the item is in fact magical, and means a mage might need to cast it twice (once to detect magic and once to scrutinize).</p>\n<h3>Attuning</h3>\n<p>A hero who wishes to wield a magical item and benefit from it's power must first attune himself. Attunement can only happen after knowledge of the items powers and benefits has been discerned. The hero must then spend one hour with the item, and they are then attuned to it an may use it's powers.</p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:1.125em\">Common Magic Item Rules</span></h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Active Powers are Actions:</strong> An item that requires a Trait roll is an action unless it says otherwise. Critical Failure means the user takes Fatigue (and loses a charge if the item has them).</li>\n<li><strong>Edges and Abilities:</strong> If an item grants an Edge or Monstrous Ability and the wielder already has that Edge, it grants the improved version (if there is one).</li>\n<li><strong>Minor and Major Powers:</strong> Some items grant minor or major powers as listed with the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Powers Summary List]{Powers}. A <em>minor</em> power automatically activates with the effect of a standard success, and a <em>major</em> power activates with the effect of a raise (no Trait roll is made). Unless the item says otherwise, this is an action and the effect lasts for the power’s full Duration and cannot be maintained.</li>\n<li><strong>Stacking:</strong> If two sources would increase a Trait, use only the highest modifier (effects don’t stack). Increases to a Trait from a magic item’s effects don’t count for determining Trait Advancements. They do affect secondary statistics like Parry or Toughness, however.</li>\n<li><strong>Multiple Items:</strong> A character can only wear one magic item in each location (head, eyes, shoulders, neck, chest, belt, wrists, hands, feet). Putting on a second necklace or a second belt, for example, has no effect. The exception to this rule is rings. A character can wear two rings and benefit from both magical effects.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Enemies with Magic Items</h3>\n<p>Enemy characters and monsters equipped with enchanted and magical items have the bonuses conferred by those items built into their profiles.</p>\n<p>So an evil knight wearing plate armor enchanted with the Aegis enchantment, for example, might have a Toughness of 12(5), where the plate armor's bonus of +4 has already been increased by the Aegis enchantment's +1.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-links-title\">Articles on Magic Items</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic Items]{Using Magic Items}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Purchasing Magic Items]{Purchasing Magic Items}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Enchantments]{Enchantments}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crafting Magic Items]{Crafting Magic Items}</h3>\n</div>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/people/artificer-infusing-armor.webp\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":2},"cf":{"id":"temp_otr25ys05qi","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic Items","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"KotQOseBZ7sAWykR","name":"Mithral","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Mithral</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>A rare metal on Eberron, mithral is forged like steel but weighs much less. Mithral reduces the Minimum Strength of weapons, armor, and shields one die type (this stacks with the bonus from masterwork). Weapons and shields made primarily of mithral (GM's call) cost 100 times normal, while armor costs 10 times normal per piece.</p>\n<p>Mithral weapons count as silver for purposes of creatures with a silver @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Weakness]{Weakness}.</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_ebw221m1i2","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/2.2. Materials and Craftsmanship","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"KxFfUAb8Xj8zlzRK","name":"Elf","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Elf</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Tens of thousands ofyears ago, the elves of the distant continent of Xen'drik rose up against the giants who ruled over them. This rebellion is the defining event in elf history. As the ancient war progressed, the magebreeders of the giants bound magic into the elves who remained loyal to them, forming the drow-assassins bred to prey on their other kin. Ultimately, the elves fled from Xen'drik and settled the island nation of Aerenal, where they split into two distinct cultures: the introspective Aereni and the warlike Tairnadal. Thus, a war nearly forty thousand years ago established the pattern of how elves live today.</p>\n<p>Neither the Aereni nor the Tairnadal (which include the elves of Valenar) have much interest in human activities, but small numbers of elves have immigrated to Khorvaire over the centuries and have more or less integrated with the cultures of the Five Nations. The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Elf, Drow]{drow}, though, are virtually unknown on Khorvaire.</p>\n<p>As a whole, elves are driven by tradition and respect for the past. Where humans value innovation, elves strive to master and perfect the techniques of their ancestors over the course of studies lasting centuries. Elf society has changed little over the last five thousand years, while Khorvaire is constantly evolving. Whatever the origin of your elf character, consider your relationship wit.h the past: Do you value the traditions ofyour ancestors? Or do you fear that your people are too mired in the past, and need to find a way to adapt and move forward?</p>\n<h3>Elves of the Five Nations</h3>\n<p>Throughout history, elves have occasionally migrated to live among the other peoples of Khorvaire. On rare occasions, entire families have relocated (as House Phiarlan did, almost three thousand years ago), but more often wanderers and exiles have come to Khorvaire and made their way there.</p>\n<p>As an elf born and raised in Khorvaire, your character has grown up among the shorter-lived races. You might not be as concerned with history and tradition as the Aereni and Tairnadal; you could even live your life entirely in the moment, with no care for your family or your legacy. Or you could be fascinated by the history and traditions ofyour ancestors and try to relearn the ways your family has forgotten.</p>\n<p>Consider also whether you've outlived human friends and how that might affect you. Did you know the parents or grandparents of another member of your party? Are you trying to repay a debt or fulfill a promise to that long-dead friend, or are you trying to recapture some spark of the friendship you felt years ago? Do you remember a time before the Last War? Did you fight in the war?</p>\n<h3>Elves and Dragonmarks</h3>\n<p>The <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Shadow]{Mark of Shadow}</em> first appeared among the elves of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Phiarlan]{Phiarlan} line, and the house quickly turned the mark's powers of shadow and illusion into an economic dynasty. The suspicion of their kin drove them from Aerenal to Khorvaire, and the house splintered during the Last War, giving rise to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Thuranni]{House Thuranni}. The two houses of shadow control the business of espionage throughout Khorvaire, but they also operate more legitimate ventures related to art and entertainment.</p>\n<p>Phiarlan blood still runs among some of the Aereni elves, and the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Shadow]{Mark of Shadow}</em><em> </em>appears once or twice in each elven generation. Elves bearing this mark are always inducted into the elite force of the Cairdal Bladesan espionage agency in the service of Aerenal's Sibling Kings.</p>\n<h3>Aereni and Tairnadal</h3>\n<p>For thousands of years, the island nation of Aerenal has been ruled and protected by the godlike power of the Undying Court, a council of undead high elves. The greatest heroes of the Aereni join the Undying Court after death, joining their heroic ancestors in immortality.</p>\n<p>Tairnadal elves dedicate themselves to the arts of war. The greatest heroes of the Tairnadal's many wars-against giants, dragons, and the champions of Dhakaan—live on after death, becoming the patron ancestors of the Tairnadal. Upon reaching adulthood, a Tairnadal elf forms a bond with one of these ancestors and strives to follow in the footsteps of this ancestor, living as the patron did. In this way, the champion comes to embody their ancestor, allowing the dead to live on.</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Agile:</strong> Elves are graceful and agile. They start with a d6 in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} instead of a d4. This increases maximum @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} to d12+1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Elven Magical Nature]{Elven Magical Nature}:</strong> Elves were born of ancient giant magic and have an inherent connection to arcane energies. Elves get a free reroll when rolling to resist enemy powers.</li>\n<li><strong>Keen Senses:</strong> Elves have exceptionally keen senses. They add +1 to any @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} check.</li>\n<li><strong>Intelligence:</strong> Elves are highly intelligent and long-lived. They start with a d6 in Smarts instead of a d4. This increases maximum Smarts to d12 + 1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Language}: </strong>Elves from Aerenal or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Valenar]{Valenar} start with a d8 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Elvish} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Common}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}:</strong> Elves eyes amplify light like a cat's, allowing them to see in the dark. Low Light Vision ignores up –2 penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness} remains unaffected.</li>\n<li><strong>Slender: </strong>Elves are graceful but more frail than other races. Their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} is reduced by 1 and they have a −1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} checks.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/elf.webp\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/elf.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L4NqGfd9AVja33DY"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":2},"cf":{"id":"temp_di56kj2145l","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"L7RLEvVFAWYxJIRY","name":"Archeologist","content":"<p>An archaeologist learns about the long-lost and fallen cultures of the past by studying their remains -their bones, their ruins, their surviving masterworks, and their tombs. Those who practice archaeology travel to the far corners of Eberron to root through crumbled cities and lost dungeons, digging in search of artifacts that might tell the stories of monarchs and high priests, wars and cataclysms, and most importantly, their magic and technology.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Athletics, Fighting, Language, Lore, Notice, Persuasion, Religion, Research, Science, Shooting, Stealth, Survival</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Alertness, Brave, Linguist</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Artifact Hunter, Explorer, Investigator, Scholar, Thief</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Scavenger</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.hW3xL2LcVGgDuDwA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"LHDtUPSeEN7w6l4I","name":"Melee Weapons Table","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table gear-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Melee Weapons</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Type</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Damage</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Min Str.</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Weight</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Cost</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Notes</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"table-column-header table-subheader-center\" colspan=\"6\" scope=\"colgroup\"><span class=\"table-subheader-center-wrapper table-subheader-center-content\">Simple Weapons</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Club, Great]{Club, Great}</td>\n<td>Str+d8</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>1 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{Two hands}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Club, Heavy]{Club, Heavy}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>7 sp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Club, Light]{Club, Light}</td>\n<td>Str+d4</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>2 sp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Dagger]{Dagger}</td>\n<td>Str+d4</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>2 gp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Mace]{Mace}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>5 gp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Mace, Heavy]{Mace, Heavy}</td>\n<td>Str+d8</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>12 gp</td>\n<td>AP 1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Morning Star]{Morning Star}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>8 gp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Quarterstaff]{Quarterstaff}</td>\n<td>Str+d4</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>2 sp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} +1, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} 1, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{two hands}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Sap]{Sap}</td>\n<td>Str+d4</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>5 sp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Nonlethal Damage]{Nonlethal damage} only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Spear, Short]{Spear, Short}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>1 gp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Whip]{Whip}</td>\n<td>Str+d4</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} –1, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} 2, with a raise on the attack roll the victim is Entangled instead of rolling bonus damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"table-column-header table-subheader-center\" colspan=\"6\" scope=\"colgroup\"><span class=\"table-subheader-center-wrapper table-subheader-center-content\">Martial Weapons</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Axe, Battle]{Axe, Battle}</td>\n<td>Str+d8</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Axe, Great]{Axe, Great}</td>\n<td>Str+d10</td>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>7</td>\n<td>30 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} 3, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} –1, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{two hands}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Axe, Hand]{Axe, Hand}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Falchion]{Falchion}</td>\n<td>Str+d8</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>40 gp</td>\n<td>Two hands</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Maul]{Maul}</td>\n<td>Str+d10</td>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>20 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} 2, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{Two hands}, +2 damage to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{break objects}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Rapier]{Rapier}</td>\n<td>Str+d4</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>25 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} +1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Scimitar]{Scimitar}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>15 gp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Sword, Bastard]{Sword, Bastard}</td>\n<td>Str+d8</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>35 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} 1, may be used @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{Two hands} (if so, it may Sweep and cause +1 damage)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Sword, Great]{Sword, Great}</td>\n<td>Str+d10</td>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} 2, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{Two hands}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Sword, Long]{Sword, Long}</td>\n<td>Str+d8</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>15 gp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Sword, Short]{Sword, Short}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.War Pick]{War Pick}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Warhammer]{Warhammer}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} 1, +1 damage to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{break objects}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"table-column-header table-subheader-center\" colspan=\"6\" scope=\"colgroup\"><span class=\"table-subheader-center-wrapper table-subheader-center-content\">Polearm Weapons</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Glaive]{Glaive}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} 1, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{two hands}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Halberd]{Halberd}</td>\n<td>Str+d8</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>20 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} 1, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{two hands}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Lance]{Lance}</td>\n<td>Str+d8</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} 2 when charging, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} 2, only usable in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mounted Combat]{Mounted Combat}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Pike]{Pike}</td>\n<td>Str+d8</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>18</td>\n<td>5 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} 2, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{two hands}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Spear]{Spear}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>2 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} 1. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} +1 if used @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{two-handed}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Trident]{Trident}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>15 gp</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} 1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"table-column-header table-subheader-center\" colspan=\"6\" scope=\"colgroup\"><span class=\"table-subheader-center-wrapper table-subheader-center-content\">Exotic Weapons</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Alchemy Blade]{Alchemy Blade}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>310 gp</td>\n<td>+1d6 damage from fire or frost.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Cane, Monk's]{Cane, Monk's}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>25 gp</td>\n<td>+1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} rolls or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} attempts</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Cane, Sword]{Cane, Sword}</td>\n<td>Str+d6</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>15 gp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Cat-o-Nine Tails]{Cat-o-Nine Tails}</td>\n<td>Str+d4</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>7 gp</td>\n<td>—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Flute, Steel]{Flute, Steel}</td>\n<td>Str+d4</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<