{"_id":"VrjXvee8KFg6e8G6","name":"Hobgoblin","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Hobgoblin</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>The goblinoid species-goblins, hobgoblins, and bugbears—were once the dominant civilization in Khorvaire, with the goblinoid Empire of Dhakaan ruling the continent for thousands of years. It was crippled by a long conflict with the daelkyr and their aberrant armies; even though the daelkyr were defeated, the seeds of madness took root in the empire and tore it apart. Today there are four primary goblinoid cultures in Khorvaire.</p>\n<p>Among the <em>dar</em> or goblin people, hobgoblins are known as <em>ghaal'dar</em> or \"mighty people\". Hobgoblins are the most organized and intelligent of the goblinoid species, often holding the positions of power and organization.</p>\n<h3>The Ghaal'dar</h3>\n<p>The Ghaal'dar tribes arose from the remnants of the Dhakaani Empire. Hobgoblins are the leaders of the Ghaal'dar, enforcing their will on their goblin and bugbear peers. The history of the Ghaal'dar is filled with strife; when they weren't fighting Galifar or Zilargo, the tribes usually turned on one another. This came to an end with the Last War. House Deneith hired Ghaal'dar mercenaries, and this gave focus to the divided tribes. A brilliant hobgoblin, Haruuc, united the Ghaal'dar, and under his leadership they seized control of what is now Darguun. The aging Lhesh Haruuc remains as the ruler of Darguun, and many fear that his death could throw the region into chaos.</p>\n<p>As a Ghaal'dar goblinoid, you hold your place through cunning and strength. You may have been a former mercenary now seeking adventure. You could be working as an emissary for one of the Ghaal'dar tribes or even Lhesh Haruuc himself. Or you could have been driven from your tribe by the actions of a rival; perhaps you're seeking allies to reclaim your birthright.</p>\n<h3>The Heirs of Dhakaan</h3>\n<p>Though the Dhakaani Empire defeated the alien daelkyr, the war left seeds ofcorruption strewn throughout the empire. As Dhakaan began to fall, a number of generals and governors gathered their forces and retreated into shelters deep within the earth, determined to preserve their civilization until the Empire could finally be restored. After thousands of years, their descendants have finally emerged, competing among themselves to determine which leader deserves the imperial crown. Once this is settled, they will turn to the conquest of Darguun and Khorvaire.</p>\n<p>The Dhakaani are far fewer in number than the Ghaal'dar; they had to carefully limit their population in the underground vaults they've dwelled in for the past age. However, they have held onto the martial discipline and techniques that allowed their ancestors to dominate the continent. Their weaponsmiths are superior even to the artificers of House Cannith, and they are experts in the working of adamantine and other exotic metals. Anyone who presumes to look down upon goblinoids should be surprised by the skills of the Dhakaani.</p>\n<p>The Heirs of Dhakaan are an agnostic society and don't have clerics, paladins, or druids. Their focus is on martial excellence, and their spiritual leaders are bards, who tell tales of past glory. Among the Dhakaan, goblinoids work together. Hobgoblins are the strategists and commanders, typically having the skills of fighters, bards, or rangers. Bugbears cultivate a focused battle rage and are typically barbarians. Goblins are largely artisans and laborers, but exceptional goblins join the khesh'dar (\"silent folk\"), learning the skills of rogues, monks, or rangers. The khesh'dar spread agents across the Five Nations, and one can never know when a city goblin might turn out to be an assassin.</p>\n<p>As an adventurer from a Dhakaani clan, consider why are you working with the other player characters? Are you a scout gathering information? Are you searching for allies to defeat a rival clan, or to support your own unlikely bid for the Imperial throne? Are you an exile? If so, do you hope to regain your position, or have you abandoned your ties to the Dhakaani?</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}:</strong> Hobgoblin eyes are accustomed to the dark of Khyber. Darkvision ignores up to –4 penalties for all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} up to 10\" away. Beyond 10\" they ignore up to –2 penalties. Such vision is in black and white (monchrome) only.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Language}: </strong>Hobgoblins start with a d8 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Goblin} instead of <span style=\"color:#191813\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Common}.</span></li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Martial Training]{Martial Training}:</strong> Hobgoblin are trained in war as soon as they can hold a weapon in their hand. They start with a d4 in one skill of their choice from <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}</em>, or <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}</em>. If the skill is a core skill this will increase the skill's maximum to d12+1.</li>\n<li><strong>Warrior Trained: </strong>Hobgoblins are born and bred as warriors and leaders. Hobgoblins begin play with one free Combat or Leadership @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edge}.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/hobgoblin.webp\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/hobgoblin.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.Xml542xziJ7D56S8"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":2},"cf":{"id":"temp_di56kj2145l","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"WBLcCNrEQHf5jfWq","name":"Armor and Swimming","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Armor and Swimming</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>It is particularly difficult to swim while wearing armor. Characters subtract any Encumbrance penalties as usual from the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Swimming) rolls, but also subtract the natural bonus of any armor worn as well. Ignore magical bonuses, considering only the bonus of a basic suit of that type.</p>\n<p>A suit of leather, for example, adds +1 to the user’s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}, and so subtracts –1 from his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Swimming) rolls.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-links-title\">Ship Setting Rules</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor and Swimming]{Armor and Swimming}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cabin Fever]{Cabin Fever}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Careening]{Careening}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Pay]{Crew Pay}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Provisions]{Crew Provisions}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fighting Below Deck]{Fighting Below Deck}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{Nautical Contact}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Navigation]{Navigation}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Fire]{Ship Fire}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Repairs]{Ship Repairs}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Storms at Sea]{Storms at Sea}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_500ev3usjom","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Nautical Campaigns","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"WBLgzqujVw1w1mOF","name":"Abyssal Bloodline","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Abyssal</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Generations ago, a demon corrupted the hero’s heritage. She has @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Enviromental Resistance]{enviromental resistance} to electricity, +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}, and sharp claws that cause Str+d4, AP 2 damage.</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>★ Advanced Form: </strong>The abyssal can conjure demons to aid her. The cost for s@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{summon ally} is reduced by 2 (to a minimum of 1), and the entities summoned cause @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Fear]{Fear}. She also gains @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Enviromental Resistance]{enviromental resistance} to cold, fire, and electricity.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_w2j6cd7pbcs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.4. Bloodlines","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"WJs8tQhTJwgNgPfP","name":"Pilot/Ship Captain","content":"<p>Commanders and pilots of elemental bound vehicles, such as lightning rails, wind galleons, or the new air ships. Pilots are often members of House Lyrandar or House Orien. However there are those who are just teamsters in caravans, or ship masters from the Lhazaar Principalities.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Athletics, Boating, Common Knowledge, Cosmology, Gambling, Piloting, Repair</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Natural Swimmer</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Any leadership edge</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Ace, Acrobat, Boarder, Rope Monkey</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Storm Chaser, Wind Sense</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.7w65EIgR0PjvvXF0"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"WgsZrMpvPDwBfgXi","name":"Human","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Human</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>The first human settlers came to Khorvaire about 3,000 years ago, landing in the area now known as the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Lhazaar Principalities]{Lhazaar Principalities}. From there, they began a slow but inexorable spread across the continent, disrupting the placid elven empire of Aerenal and leaving further ruined remnants of fallen Dhakaani goblin kingdoms in their wake. During this migration, they founded the settlements that would grow into the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Five Nations]{Five Nations}. Even today humans make up the majority of the population in these countries. Despite their relatively short lifespans—or perhaps because of them—humans are innovative, adaptable, and aggressive, always pushing their limits and pursuing new ideas.</p>\n<p>Humans prove extremely diverse; a barbarian from the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Demon Wastes]{Demon Wastes} has little in common with a Brelish rogue. When creating a human character, consider where you're from and how that's reflected in your class and background. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Aundair]{Aundair} is a logical place of origin for a wizard character, but your wizard could be a down-andout arcanist from the alleys of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Sharn]{Sharn} or a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Lhazaar Principalities]{Lhazaar} pirate with a knack for the mystic arts.</p>\n<h3>Humans and Dragonmarks</h3>\n<p>Five different dragonmarks appear among humans, reflecting their dominant status among the races of Khorvaire:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Making]{Mark of Making} </em>is found in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Cannith]{House Cannith}, which has used it to become one of the most powerful houses, creating an abundance of both magical and technological wonders.</li>\n<li>The <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Handling]{Mark of Handling} </em>appears in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Vadalis]{House Vadalis}, which uses it to breed fine mounts and other creatures.</li>\n<li>The <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Passage]{Mark of Passage} </em>aids the humans of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Orien]{House Orien} in operating the lightning rail and trade caravans running across the continent.</li>\n<li>The <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Sentinel]{Mark of Sentinel} </em>makes the bodyguards, mercenaries, and Sentinel Marshals of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Deneith]{House Deneith} widely respected across Khorvaire.</li>\n<li>Humans also number among @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Tharashk]{House Tharashk} and manifest the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Finding]{Mark of Finding}</em> with their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-orc]{half-orc} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{orc} kin.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Adaptable: </strong>umans are extremely easy to adapt and learn new things. They begin play with one free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edge}. They must meet all the requirements for the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edge} as usual. They also gain a d6 in any one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Attribute} instead of a d4. This does <em>not</em> increase the attribute limit.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Language}:</strong> Humans from Sarlona start with a d8 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Riedran} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Common}.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/human.webp\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/human.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.p3IjYDRfpFs5fvXk"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_di56kj2145l","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"WraAjojcW3QT4Mn4","name":"Barbarian","content":"<p>Even in these enlightened times, primal warriors linger on the edges of Khorvaire. Fearsome fighters, defined by durability, speed, instinct, and the ability to channel oneself into a physical frenzy. Traditionally barbarians are savage champions of cultures seen as primitive, relying on force and fury in place of sophisticated techniques.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Athletics, Fighting, Intimidation, Notice, Riding, Stealth, Survival</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Alertness, Berserk, True Berserker, Brawny, Brute</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Any combat edge</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Monster Hunter</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Humiliate, Provoke, Strong Willed, Iron Will</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Danger Sense, Liquid Courage</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.OwFGvHEjm9cHtgDD"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"X3HTifMkEwLlwKTi","name":"Ammo Table","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table gear-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Ammo</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ammo</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Cost</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Weight</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" style=\"text-align:left\" scope=\"col\">Notes</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Arrow]{Arrow}</td>\n<td>5 cp</td>\n<td>.05 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Arrow, Alchemist's Acid]{Arrow, Alchemist's Acid}</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n<td>.2 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Explode in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template} causing 2d4 acid damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Arrow, Alchemist's Fire]{Arrow, Alchemist's Fire}</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n<td>.2 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Explode in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template} causing 2d4 fire damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Arrow, Alchemist's Frost]{Arrow, Alchemist's Frost}</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n<td>.2 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Explode in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template} causing 2d4 frost damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Arrow, Alchemist's Spark]{Arrow, Alchemist's Spark}</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n<td>.2 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Explode in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template} causing 2d4 spark damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Arrow, Blunt]{Arrow, Blunt}</td>\n<td>4 gp/20</td>\n<td>.5 lbs/20</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Non-lethal damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Arrow, Grappling]{Arrow, Grappling}</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n<td>.5 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Half range.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Arrow, Smoke]{Arrow, Smoke}</td>\n<td>15 gp</td>\n<td>.25 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Fills a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template} with smoke.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Arrow, Sticky]{Arrow, Sticky}</td>\n<td>40 gp</td>\n<td>.25 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Alchemical arrow that <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{entangles}</em> a single target.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Arrow, Whistling]{Arrow, Whistling}</td>\n<td>1 sp</td>\n<td>.05 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Emit a keening sound audible within 30\" of it's flight path.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Bolt]{Bolt}</td>\n<td>5 cp</td>\n<td>.05 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">—</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Bolt, Alchemist's Acid]{Bolt, Alchemist's Acid}</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n<td>.2 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Explode in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template} causing 2d4 acid damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Bolt, Alchemist's Fire]{Bolt, Alchemist's Fire}</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n<td>.2 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Explode in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template} causing 2d4 fire damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Bolt, Alchemist's Frost]{Bolt, Alchemist's Frost}</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n<td>.2 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Explode in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template} causing 2d4 frost damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Bolt, Alchemist's Spark]{Bolt, Alchemist's Spark}</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n<td>.2 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Explode in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template} causing 2d4 spark damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Bolt, Grappling]{Bolt, Grappling}</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n<td>.5 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">Half range.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Sling Bullets]{Sling Bullets}</td>\n<td>1 cp</td>\n<td>.05 lbs</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left\">—</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ib2qus6sn1","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/2.1. Gear Tables","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":2}}}
{"_id":"XNUtg8SGOTzQVuBT","name":"Wizard","content":"<p>As a wizard, you’re an arcane scientist and, like any scientist, you could be diligent, eccentric, or even stark-raving mad. Among the other magically inclined, you have every reason to be proud of your talents. Bards? Stage magicians obsessed with fame. Sorcerers? Freaks who won the genetic lottery. You earned your power. You’re a bona fide genius and it’s unlikely that anyone will soon forget how bright your brilliance burned, especially if you go out in a fireball of glory.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Arcana, Common Knowledge, Cosmology, Language, Lore, Science, Spellcasting</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Arcane Background (Magic), Arcane Resistance, Improved Arcane Resistance, Linguist, University Trained</p>\n<p><strong>Power Edges:</strong> Channeling, Concentration, Power Surge, Wizard</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Familiar, Scholar</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.23nhljaxcjJ23SWE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"Xmyol3CnHsjJ0ZeJ","name":"Spy","content":"<p>The lords, nobles, dragonmarked houses and wealthy merchants of the cities of Khorvaire like to keep tabs on one another, probing for weaknesses and looking for ways to take advantage of each other. They often send spies to infiltrate their enemies, who work undercover and send back reports to their employers. A spy often pretends to be of another profession as a means to remain undetected.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Athletics, Common Knowledge, Fighting, Gambling, Intimidation, Performance, Persuasion, Shooting, Stealth, Thievery</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Alertness, Charismatic, Linguist, Quick</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Escape Artist, Honey-Tongue, Investigator, Jack-of-all-Trades, Thief</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Connections, Streetwise</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.bK89SODAdsBQv317"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"YMpFKQTMh1Wl0ze1","name":"Animal Domain","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Animal Domain</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Aspects:</strong> Animals, beasts, hunting, rangers, wilderness</li>\n<li><strong>Deities:</strong> Balinor</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Accelerate Healing]{Accelerate Healing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Analyze Foe]{Analyze Foe}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Augury]{Augury}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{Beast Friend}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{Blind}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{Burst}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{Conjure Item}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Damage Field]{Damage Field}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Divination]{Divination}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{Elemental Manipulation}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{Empathy} (animals only)</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{Entangle}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Environmental Protection]{Environmental Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{Farsight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fear]{Fear}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Growth/Shrink]{Growth/Shrink}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{Havoc}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{Healing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{Invisibility}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Leaping]{Leaping}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Light/Darkness}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{Locate}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message]{Message} (animal trapping only)</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{Relief}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sanctuary]{Sanctuary}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{Sentry}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Shape Change]{Shape Change}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Sloth/Speed}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{Sound/Silence}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{Speak Language} (animals and plants only)</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{Stun}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{Summon Beast}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{Warrior's Gift}</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0bt6afhtf6wi","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.2. Domains","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"YU1UTBg9bfeVwQKw","name":"Monk","content":"<p>Beginning with a foundation of mental and physical discipline, a monk channels energy to force an impossible action to become possible, from moving with superhuman speed to striking with fists of flame. The monk focuses power within them and becomes a conduit with the strictest discipline.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Athletics, Fighting, Faith or Psionics, Notice, Religion, Stealth</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Arcane Background (Miracles or Psionics), Fleet-Footed, Quick</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Counterattack, Improved Counterattack, Free Runner, Martial Artist, Martial Warrior</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Power Edges:</strong> Holy/Unholy Warrior</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Acrobat, Guardian, Holy Adept</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Strong Willed, Iron Will</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Chi, Danger Sense</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.hUQGZcxPSlD3LK6T"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"YlQ8wzGsRiFRNjYL","name":"Tiefling","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Tiefling</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Many tieflings are born to the Carrion Tribes, the barbarians who live in the Demon Wastes. Such tieflings are touched by the fiendish forces bound beneath the Wastes, and the tribes consider them to be blessed. If you're playing such a tiefling, why have you left the Wastes? It could be that you were destined for some evil purpose-perhaps even serving as an avatar for an imprisoned Overlord-and you are fleeing that destiny.</p>\n<p>Other tieflings are shaped not by fiendish powers, but by the influence of the fiend-tainted planes. Such tieflings might be born in manifest zones, where a plane exerts influence over a region. Planar tieflings are oddities, often seen as strange but not necessarily evil.</p>\n<p>Finally, the Venomous Demesne—a city-state hidden on the far side of Droaam—is populated by tieflings. These tieflings descend from Sarlonan mages who bargained with dark powers, with the Demesne's lords being powerful warlocks and wizards. The Venomous Demesne has had no significant contact with the Five Nations and few know it exists. Your character could be an envoy or exile from it, or simply an adventurer driven by a desire to see what lies beyond your homeland.</p>\n<h3>Self-Reliant and Suspicious</h3>\n<p>Tieflings rarely appear in the cities and towns of Khorvaire, with most dwelling at the fringes of civilization. Tieflings subsist in small minorities found mostly in human cities or towns, often in the roughest quarters of those places, where they grow up to be swindlers, thieves, or crime lords. Sometimes they live among other minority populations in enclaves where they are treated with more respect.</p>\n<p>Lacking a homeland, tieflings know that they have to make their own way in the world and that they have to be strong to survive. They are not quick to trust anyone who claims to be a friend, but when a tiefling’s companions demonstrate that they trust him or her, the tiefling learns to extend the same trust to them. And once a tiefling gives someone loyalty, the tiefling is a firm friend or ally for life.</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}:</strong> Tieflings infernal heritage allows them to see into the darkness of Khyber. Darkvision ignores up to –4 penalties for all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} up to 10\" away. Beyond 10\" they ignore up to –2 penalties. Such vision is in black and white (monchrome) only.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Fiendish Sorcery]{Fiendish Sorcery}: </strong>Tieflings inherently have innate magic from their fiendish ancestry. Tieflings can choose two of the following powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{confusion}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{darkness}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{empathy}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{illusion}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Link]{mind link}</em>, or <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{puppet}</em>.\n<p>The tiefling has 10 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} that recharge normally. As a limited free action, they automatically activate the power with a success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} for an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}.  They may use applicable <strong>Power Modifiers </strong>if desired.</p>\n<p>Fiendish Sorcery doesn’t grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If they also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} can be used with Fiendish Sorcery (and vice-versa).</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Infernal Resistance]{Infernal Resistance}: </strong>Due to Teiflings infernal heritage they recieve a +1 bonus to resist acid, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cold]{cold}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heat]{heat} and fire effects. Damage from these sources is also reduced by 1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Language}:</strong> Tieflings may start with a d8 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Infernal} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Common}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Outsider (Tiefling)]{Outsider (Major)}:</strong> Tieflings are viewed with heavy suspicious in most areas of civilizied culture. Tieflings have a –2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{persuasion} rolls made to influence those who aren't their kind. They also have very few is any legal rights in most civilized nations.</li>\n<li><strong>Spirited:</strong> Tieflings have a strength of spirit and willpower. They start with a d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} instead of a d4. This increases maximum @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} to d12+1.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/tiefling.webp\" /></div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/tiefling.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.9HqI82YeMZdTAeIK"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":5},"cf":{"id":"temp_di56kj2145l","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"Yq1zbc1vsRzjCojQ","name":"Orc","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Orc</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Thousands of years beforc humans came to Khorvaire, the land was dominated by wild orcs and goblinoids of the Dhakaani Empire. The goblin empire scattered the orc tribes and forced them into harsh and unwanted lands: the swamps of the Shadow Marches, the Demon Wastes, and the depths of the Ironroot Mountains. But in the Shadow Marches, the orcs learned the secrets of druidic magic from the dragon Vvaraak, becoming the first of the Gatekeepers. With the invasion of the alien daelkyr from Xoriat, the Gatekeepers put the dragon's teaching to the test, creating magical seals that bound the daelkyr in the depths of Khyber and protected Eberron against further incursion from the plane of madness.</p>\n<p>Three prominent groups of orcs have survived into the present age:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The Ghaash'kala are servants of the Silver Flame (which they call Kalok Shash, the \"binding flame\"), who devote their lives to battling the fiends of the Demon Wastes. Humans from the Carrion Tribes of the wastes sometimes hear the call ofKalok Shash and join the Ghaash'kala, leading to a significant population of half-orcs there.</li>\n<li>The Jhorash'tar orcs are a perpetual threat in and around the Ironroot Mountains, shaped by their resentment of the Mror dwarves who drove them underground. These orcs are isolated from humans, so half-orcs here are rare.</li>\n<li>The Shadow Marches holds the largest numbers of orcs and the most significant population of half-orcs.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Orcs of the Shadow Marches</h3>\n<p>The orc Gatekeepers played a crucial role in defeating the daelkyr and binding their evil in Khyber, and their descendants continue to maintain the ancient seals and fight aberrations spawned by the daelkyr's corruption. However, many orcs succumbed to that same corruption and embraced the madness of the cults of the Dragon Below. orcs who follow both of these paths continue to live in the Shadow Marches, and centuries of battles between them have diminished both sides.</p>\n<p>Humans settled in the Shadow Marches long ago, and the first half-orcs helped to cement the bond between these outsiders and the native orcs. Certain Marcher clans contain humans, orcs, and half-orcs in roughly equal numbers.</p>\n<p>When playing an orc or half-orc character from the Shadow Marches, consider what circumstances brought you into the wider world. The Leaving the Shadow Marches table offers some inspiration.</p>\n<h3>Half-orcs and Dragonmarks</h3>\n<p>The <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Finding]{Mark of Finding}</em> appears among orcs of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Tharashk]{House Tharashk}. Dragonmarked orcs work extensively with humans and half-orcs in pursuit of the house's mission of bounty hunting, inquisitive work, and prospecting. Across Khorvaire, anyone who wants to find something or someone turns to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Tharashk]{House Tharashk}.</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Brutish Size: </strong>Orcs are naturally strong. They start with a d6 in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of a d4. This increases their maximum @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} to d12+1 Additionally, they are larger than humans standing about 6 1/2-7 1/2 feet tall, increasing their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (and therefore their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}) by 1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Language}: </strong>Orcs may start with a d8 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Dwarven}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Goblin} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Orcish} depending on where they are from, instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Common}.</li>\n<li><strong><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}</strong>:</strong> Orc eyes are accustomed hunting at night, having eye's similiar to a cats. Low Light Vision ignores up –2 penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness} remains unaffected.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Primal Brute]{Primal Brute}: </strong>Orcs focus on core strength and fitness over coordination and flexibility. They treat @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} as linked to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} for purposes of Advancement. The character may also resist @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests} with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} if she chooses. Finally, Orcs increase the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Short Range} of any thrown item by +1. Double that for the adjusted @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Medium Range} , and double again for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Long Range}. If a thrown item’s Range is 3/6/12, for example, an Orc's Range is 4/8/16.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Primal Passion]{Primal Passion (Major)}: </strong>Orcs are reactive and driven by a primal passion. They often take action without thinking things through.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/orc.webp\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/orc.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.PIgr30tajsiG03nz"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":6},"cf":{"id":"temp_di56kj2145l","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"ZTDoRmjFdaQlHYKl","name":"Masterwork","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Masterwork</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Masterwork items are finely crafted versions of normal gear made by top artisans.</p>\n<p>Weapons of masterwork quality are +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP}. Masterwork melee and ranged weapons add 300 gp to the cost.</p>\n<p>Masterwork arrows, bolts, or other ammunition subtract 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} penalty at Long or Extreme @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range}, and cost six additional gold pieces per unit. Masterwork ammunition loses its bonus after use even if recovered.</p>\n<p>Armor and shields of masterwork quality reduce the Minimum Strength requirement by one die type, to a minimum of d4. Shields cost an extra 300 gp, while armor costs an extra 150 gp <em>per piece</em>.</p>\n<p>You can’t usually upgrade existing armor, weapons, or shields to masterwork quality— they must be crafted to high standards from the beginning.</p>\n<p>The availability of masterwork items — whether for sale in the marketplace or commissioned — depends on the size of the settlement and is up to the GM. Such items typically take twice as long to create if commissioned.</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_ebw221m1i2","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/2.2. Materials and Craftsmanship","color":"#000000"}}}
