{"_id":"bCBranKvgOoaQUSN","name":"Ship Fire","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Ship Fire</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Fires are very dangerous on ships and kill far more men than cannon shots usually account for. When a ship suffers a Chassis hit, it’s actually been hit in the hull somewhere. The shot itself can start a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fire]{fire}, or it might knock over necessary lanterns and candles.</p>\n<p>Roll 1d6 at the beginning of each round for each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fire]{fire} to see what effect it has on the ship.</p>\n<table class=\"table value=table\" style=\"width:70%\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Fire Table</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">[[/r 1d6]]</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Result</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fire]{Fire} burns out.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2-4</td>\n<td>The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fire]{fire} continues to burn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fire]{fire} causes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fire]{fire} spreads, making two fires.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Fighting Fires:</strong> Crews can put out fires, but this takes away from their other duties to do so.</p>\n<p>A team equal to half the ship’s base @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} (ignore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor} and magical bonuses) is required. The team must assemble one round, and the next may make a group @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} roll at –2 for one fire. With a success, the team extinguishes the fire.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-links-title\">Ship Setting Rules</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor and Swimming]{Armor and Swimming}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cabin Fever]{Cabin Fever}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Careening]{Careening}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Pay]{Crew Pay}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Provisions]{Crew Provisions}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fighting Below Deck]{Fighting Below Deck}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{Nautical Contact}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Navigation]{Navigation}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Fire]{Ship Fire}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Repairs]{Ship Repairs}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Storms at Sea]{Storms at Sea}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_500ev3usjom","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Nautical Campaigns","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"bULwbj6QAP1JwYVy","name":"Races","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"header\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p>Races</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p><cite>Savage Eberron</cite> has the following races that are available for play as player characters. All races are balanced out to +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Making Races]{racial abilities} instead of the usual +2.</p>\n<h2>Races</h2>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bugbear]{Bugbear}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Changeling]{Changeling}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dwarf]{Dwarf}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Elf]{Elf}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Gnome]{Gnome}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Goblin]{Goblin}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-elf]{Half-elf}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-orc]{Half-orc}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Halfling]{Halfling}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hobgoblin]{Hobgoblin}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Human]{Human}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{Orc}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shifter]{Shifter}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Warforged]{Warforged}</h3>\n</div>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Exotic Races</h2>\n<p>The following races are far more exotic and rare in Eberron. These require DM approval for particular campaigns.</p>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Elf, Drow]{Elf, Drow}: Xen'drik</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Eneko]{Eneko}: Sarlona</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-giant]{Half-giant}: Sarlona and Xen'drik</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Kalashtar]{Kalashtar}: Sarlona, Sharn and small other pockets</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Tiefling]{Tiefling}: Generally rare</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_intbwo9s2if","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":3}}}
{"_id":"cFaxcMKsRDvXe9s7","name":"Arcane Bloodline","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Arcane</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>The sorcerer forms a magical bond with a creature or an object. Use the rules for the wizard’s Arcane Bond.</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>★ Advanced Form: </strong>The sorcerer’s connection to magic is incredibly strong. She gets a free reroll on any @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} roll.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_w2j6cd7pbcs","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.4. Bloodlines","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"cbvyMUcqPSNAE5Hf","name":"Knowledge Domain","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Knowledge Domain</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Aspects:</strong> Knowledge, literacy, history, revealing secrets, wisdom</li>\n<li><strong>Deities:</strong> Aureon, Onatar, The Traveler, The Udying Court</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Analyze Foe]{Analyze Foe}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Augury]{Augury}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{Blind}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{Detect/Conceal Arcana}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Divination]{Divination}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{Farsight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fear]{Fear}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{Havoc}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{Healing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Light/Darkness}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{Locate}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{Lock/Unlock}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Magic Mark]{Magic Mark}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message]{Message}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Link]{Mind Link}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Reading]{Mind Reading}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Wipe]{Mind Wipe}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Object Reading]{Object Reading}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Planar Travel]{Planar Travel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{Repair}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sanctuary]{Sanctuary}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{Scrying}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Secret Writing]{Secret Writing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{Slumber}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{Sound/Silence}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{Speak Language}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{Stun}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{Summon Ally}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{Telekinesis}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{Teleport}</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0bt6afhtf6wi","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.2. Domains","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"ccnpocDWh1OSxnxO","name":"Elemental","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<h3>Weapon Enchantment</h3>\n<p>The weapon causes damage with an energy Trapping—acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic (chosen by creator).</p>\n<p><strong>Enchantment Points:</strong> 1</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 2,000 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> Damaging power with the appropiate energy trapping.</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_d6wak2736pv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/6.1. Enchantments","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"cuk99xgVS3uKgIyX","name":"Adamantine","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Adamantine</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Mined from rocks that fell from the heavens, adamantine adds +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} to any melee weapon or ranged weapon ammunition made of its metal. This stacks with the bonus from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Masterwork]{masterwork} items. Adamantine weapons cost an additional 3,000 gp.</p>\n<p>Adamantine armor is harder to pierce than that made from other materials. It ignores up to 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP}. Armor made from this material costs an extra 3,000 gp per point of armor bonus.</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_ebw221m1i2","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/2.2. Materials and Craftsmanship","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"dWSXyaErNCh2P8Km","name":"Setting Edges","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Setting Edges</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Below is a list of Edges common to most settings. You’ll find new Edges designed for your game world in official <em>Savage Worlds</em> books as well.</p>\n<p>The Edges are grouped by type to help during character creation. You’ll find a summary below.</p>\n<p>Unless an Edge specifically says otherwise, it may only be selected once.</p>\n<p>The core base Edges are those presented in <em>Pathfinder for Savage Worlds</em> rather than the <em>Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</em>.</p>\n<div>\n<h3>Altered Edges in Savage Eberron from Savage Pathfinder</h3>\n<p>The following <em>Savage Worlds</em> Edges have been altered for <em>Savage Eberron</em>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"red-text\">Arcane Background (Magic), Bard Fighter, Wizard, Pathfinder Chronicler, Pathfinder Chronicler II, Pathfinder Chronicler III</span></p>\n</div>\n<h3>Requirements</h3>\n<p>Below each Edge is the minimum Rank (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Advancement}) required to take it along with any other prerequisites such as attributes, skills, or other Edges.</p>\n</div>\n<figure class=\"figure table-figure\">\n<figcaption class=\"figure-heading\">Setting Edge Summaries</figcaption>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Class Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Artificer]{Artificer}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d6, Arcana d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Artificer Armor Restriction (Medium)]{Armor Restriction (Medium)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Artificer)]{Arcane Background (Artificer)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Enchant Magic Item]{Enchant Magic Item}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Homunculus]{Homunculus}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Infuse Item]{Infuse Item}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Powers (Artificer)]{Favored Powers (Artificer)}</td>\n<td>S, Artificer</td>\n<td>As a limited free action, the artificer may ignore up to two points of any penalties when casting <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{conjure item}</em>, or <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{repair}</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master of Artifice]{Master of Artifice}</td>\n<td>V, Artificer</td>\n<td>Spend up to 3 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} and@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Dragonshards]{Eberron dragonshard residum} to create a device that replicates another power.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Artifice Mastery]{Artifice Mastery}</td>\n<td>H, Artificer</td>\n<td>The artificer may now use Epic Power Modifiers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Barbarian]{Barbarian}</td>\n<td>N, St d6, Vi d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Barbarian Armor Restriction (Medium)]{Barbarian Armor Restriction (Medium)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fast]{Fast}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rage]{Rage}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Powerful Blow]{Powerful Blow}</td>\n<td>S, Barbarian</td>\n<td>Wild Attacks cause +4 damage instead of +2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Intimidating Glare]{Intimidating Glare}</td>\n<td>V, Barbarian</td>\n<td>The barbarian may make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} roll as a free action when dealt a Jack or better in combat.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Strength Surge]{Strength Surge}</td>\n<td>H, Barbarian</td>\n<td>The hero’s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} increases two die types when raging.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bard]{Bard}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6, Performance d4</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Bard)]{Arcane Background (Bard)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bard Armor Interference (Light)]{Armor Interference (Light)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Lore Keeper]{Lore Keeper}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sharp Tongued]{Sharp Tongued}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Inspire Heroics]{Inspire Heroics}</td>\n<td>S, Bard</td>\n<td>Once per encounter, as a limited free action, the bard gets five Inspiration tokens he can give to his allies for rerolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Countersong]{Countersong}</td>\n<td>V, Bard</td>\n<td>Allies within 5” get a free reroll when resisting or recovering from enemy spell effects.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dirge of Doom]{Dirge of Doom}</td>\n<td>H, Bard</td>\n<td>Enemy Wild Cards within 10” subtract 2 from their totals when spending a Benny.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Cleric]{Cleric}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6, Religion d4</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Cleric)]{Arcane Background (Cleric)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Channel Energy]{Channel Energy}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Destroy Undead]{Destroy Undead}</td>\n<td>S, Cleric</td>\n<td>Spend 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to create a wave of energy in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}. All undead within must make a Spirit roll or take a Wound.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Powers (Cleric)]{Favored Powers (Cleric)}</td>\n<td>V, Cleric</td>\n<td>As a limited free action, the cleric may ignore up to two points of any penalties when casting <em>healing</em>, <em>sanctuary</em>, or <em>smite</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Divine Mastery]{Divine Mastery}</td>\n<td>H, Cleric</td>\n<td>The cleric may now use Epic Power Modifiers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Druid]{Druid}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6, Animal Handling d4, Survival d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Druid)]{Arcane Background (Druid)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Druid Armor Interference (Light)]{Armor Interference (Light)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nature Bond]{Nature Bond}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nature Sense]{Nature Sense}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wild Shape]{Wild Shape}</td>\n<td>S, Druid</td>\n<td>The druid gains shape change. Duration is one hour and she casts as if one Rank higher than usual.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Powers (Druid)]{Favored Powers (Druid)}</td>\n<td>V, Druid</td>\n<td>As a limited free action, the druid may ignore up to two points of any penalties when casting <em>entangle</em>, <em>smite</em>, or <em>protection</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nature Mastery]{Nature Mastery}</td>\n<td>H, Druid</td>\n<td>The druid may now use Epic Power Modifiers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fighter]{Fighter}</td>\n<td>N, St d6, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Combat Training]{Combat Training}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Flexibility]{Martial Flexibility}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Deadly Blow]{Deadly Blow}</td>\n<td>S, Fighter</td>\n<td>The fighter adds +1 to all his damaging attacks.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Martial Flexibility]{Improved Martial Flexibility}</td>\n<td>V, Fighter</td>\n<td>The fighter may now choose two Combat Edges per encounter.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Prowess]{Martial Prowess}</td>\n<td>H, Fighter</td>\n<td>The fighter gets a free reroll on any failed Fighting roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Monk]{Monk}</td>\n<td>N, Ag d6, Sp d6, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Monk Armor Restriction (Light)]{Armor Restriction (Light)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Stunning Fist]{Stunning Fist}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Unarmed Strike]{Unarmed Strike}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Monk)]{Mystic Powers (Monk)}</td>\n<td>S, Monk</td>\n<td>The monk has 10 dedicated Power Points he can use to cast <em>boost Trait</em> (Agility, Athletics, Fighting, or Stealth), <em>deflection</em>, <em>smite</em>, and <em>speed</em>. All are self only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Great Ki]{Great Ki}</td>\n<td>V, Monk</td>\n<td>The monk's Mystic Powers now includes <em>boost Trait</em> (<em>Strength</em>), <em>protection</em>, <em>speed</em>, <em>wall walker</em>, <em>warrior's gift</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wholeness of Body]{Wholeness of Body}</td>\n<td>H, Monk</td>\n<td>The monk may spend 2 Power Points to make a Soak roll. This does not count as spending a Benny.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Paladin]{Paladin}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6, St d6, Vow</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Aura of Courage]{Aura of Courage}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Code of Honor]{Code of Honor}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Detect Evil (or Good)]{Detect Evil (or Good)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Smite Evil (or Good)]{Smite Evil (or Good)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Paladin)]{Mystic Powers (Paladin)}</td>\n<td>S, Paladin</td>\n<td>The paladin has 10 dedicated Power Points she can use to cast <em>boost Trait </em>(Fighting, Strength, Vigor), <em>healing</em>, <em>relief</em>, <em>smite</em>. All but healing and relief are self only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mercy]{Mercy}</td>\n<td>V, Paladin</td>\n<td>The paladin can remove Distracted, Vulnerable, or Shaken statuses to an ally within Range of Spirit.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mount]{Mount}</td>\n<td>H, Paladin</td>\n<td>The hero gains a loyal WC light or heavy horse.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ranger]{Ranger}</td>\n<td>N, Shooting d6, Survival d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ranger Armor Restriction (Medium)]{Armor Restriction (Medium)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Enemy]{Favored Enemy}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Terrain]{Favored Terrain}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wilderness Stride (Ranger)]{Wilderness Stride (Ranger)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Quarry]{Quarry}</td>\n<td>S, Ranger</td>\n<td>The ranger chooses an additional enemy and terrain type for his Favored Enemy and Favored Terrain abilities.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Powers (Ranger)]{Mystic Powers (Ranger)}</td>\n<td>V, Ranger</td>\n<td>The ranger has 10 dedicated Power Points he can use to cast <em>beast friend</em>, <em>boost Trait</em> (Athletics, Fighting, Shooting), <em>entangle</em>, <em>warrior's gift</em>. All but entangle are self only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Hunter]{Master Hunter}</td>\n<td>H, Ranger</td>\n<td>The hunter adds an additional d6 damage when making a successful Athletics (throwing), Fighting, or Shooting attack against their Favored Enemy.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rogue]{Rogue}</td>\n<td>N, Ag d6, Notice d6, Stealth d6, Thievery d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)]{Armor Restriction (Light)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Skill Monkey]{Skill Monkey}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trap Sense]{Trap Sense}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sneak Attack]{Sneak Attack}</td>\n<td>S, Rogue</td>\n<td>The rogue gets a chance to detect traps before springing them. She also ignores up to two points of penalties when disarming them with Thievery.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Uncanny Reflexes]{Uncanny Reflexes}</td>\n<td>V, Rogue</td>\n<td>The rogue ignores the usual –2 Agility penalty to Evasion attempts, and may attempt to Evade any area effect that doesn't usually allow it.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Opportunist]{Opportunist}</td>\n<td>H, Rogue</td>\n<td>The rogue gets a free attack against a foe who Withdraws from Melee, even if they have Extraction. If they don't have Extraction, they count as Vulnerable to her.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sorcerer]{Sorcerer}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d6, Sp d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Sorcerer)]{Arcane Background (Sorcerer)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sorcerer Armor Interference (Cloth)]{Armor Interference (Cloth)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bloodline]{Bloodline}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Powers (Sorcerer)]{Favored Powers (Sorcerer)}</td>\n<td>S, Sorcerer</td>\n<td>As a limited free action, the sorcerer may ignore up to two points of any penalties when casting <em>bolt</em>, <em>elemental manipulation</em>, or <em>protection</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sorcery Mastery]{Sorcery Mastery}</td>\n<td>V, Sorcerer</td>\n<td>The sorcerer may now use Epic Power Modifiers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Advanced Bloodline]{Advanced Bloodline}</td>\n<td>H, Sorcerer</td>\n<td>The sorcerer gains his bloodline's advanced ability.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wizard]{Wizard}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d6, Arcana d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Wizard)]{Arcane Background (Wizard)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wizard Armor Interference (Cloth)]{Armor Interference (Cloth)}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Schools]{Schools}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Spellbooks]{Spellbooks}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Bond]{Arcane Bond}</td>\n<td>S, Wizard</td>\n<td>The wizards forms an intense magical bond with an object or creature.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Mastery]{Arcane Mastery}</td>\n<td>V, Wizard</td>\n<td>The wizard may now use Epic Power Modifiers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Inspiration]{Eldritch Inspiration}</td>\n<td>H, Wizard</td>\n<td>The wizard can spend a Benny to cast any power of his Rank or lower at a –2 penalty.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Dragonmarked Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Detection]{Mark of Detection}</td>\n<td>N, Half-elf</td>\n<td>Mark of Detection with 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Augury]{augury}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost trait}</em> (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}, and any \"knowledge\" based skill only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em> (no Identify), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{locate}</em> (can only locate traps), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Reading]{mind reading}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{scrying}</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Finding]{Mark of Finding}</td>\n<td>N, Human, Half-orc, or Orc</td>\n<td>Mark of Finding with 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Analyze Foe]{analyze foe}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana} </em>(Identify only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{darksight}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{farsight}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{locate}</em>. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight} </em>and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{farsight} </em>have the range of touch only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Handling]{Mark of Handling}</td>\n<td>N, Human</td>\n<td>Mark of Handling with 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{beast friend}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em> (animals only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{empathy}</em> (animals only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{speak language} </em>(Beasts for the power only), and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{summon beast}</em>. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait}</em><em> </em>and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{speak language} </em>have the range of touch only.<em><br /></em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Healing]{Mark of Healing}</td>\n<td>N, Halfling</td>\n<td>Mark of Healing with 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Accelerate Healing]{accelerate healing}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait} </em>(@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{healing}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{survival}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> (not Mass Healing), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{relief}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Resurrection]{resurrection}</em>. All powers are touch only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Hospitality]{Mark of Hospitality}</td>\n<td>N, Halfling</td>\n<td>Mark of Hospitality with 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{conjure item}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{empathy}</em> (humanoids only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{elemental manipulation}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Planar Travel]{planar travel}</em> (Extra-dimensional space for the power only), and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{slumber}</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Making]{Mark of Making}</td>\n<td>N, Human</td>\n<td>Mark of Making with 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{Conjure item}</em> (not including Create Food and Water), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect/conceal arcana}</em> (not including Alignment Sense), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Object Reading]{object reading}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{repair}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</em> has a ranch of touch only.<em><br /></em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Passage]{Mark of Passage}</td>\n<td>N, Human</td>\n<td>Mark of Passage with 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fly]{fly}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Leaping]{leaping}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{speed}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{summon beast}</em> (mount only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{teleport}</em> (not including Teleport Foe). All powers (except <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{summon beast}</em>) have a range of touch only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Scribing]{Mark of Scribing}</td>\n<td>N, Gnome</td>\n<td>Mark of Scribing with 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{confusion}</em> (spoken or written words trapping only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Magic Mark]{magic mark}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message]{message}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Secret Writing]{secret writing}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{speak language}</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Sentinel]{Mark of Sentinel}</td>\n<td>N, Human</td>\n<td>Mark of Sentinel with 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{arcane protection}</em>,  <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em>,  <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Gift of Battle]{gift of battle}</em>,  <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{warrior's gift}</em>. All powers have the  range of touch only.<em><br /></em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Shadow]{Mark of Shadow}</td>\n<td>N, Elf</td>\n<td>Mark of Shadow with 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{darkness}</em> (including Epic Powers), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{disguise}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{illusion}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Intangibility]{intangibility}</em> (including Duration), and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{scrying}</em>. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise} </em>and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Intangibility]{intangibility}</em> are self only.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Storm]{Mark of Storm}</td>\n<td>N, Half-elf</td>\n<td>Mark of Storm with 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{barrier}</em> (air and water trapping only, not including Damage or Deadly), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{darkness}</em> (air and water trapping only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{elemental manipulation}</em> (air and water trappings only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{havoc}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{telekinesis} </em>(air and water trappings only). </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mark of Warding]{Mark of Warding}</td>\n<td>N, Dwarf</td>\n<td>Mark of Warding with 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{arcane protection}</em> (including Epic Powers), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{barrier} </em>(not including Damage), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Glyph]{glyph}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{lock/unlock}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{sentry}</em>.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Prestige Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Archer]{Arcane Archer}</td>\n<td>S, AB or Mp, Shooting d8</td>\n<td><strong>Enhance:</strong> arrows for +1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} and damage. <strong>Trapping:</strong> Give the arrow and enviromental @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trapping}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Archer II]{Arcane Archer II}</td>\n<td>V, AA</td>\n<td><strong>Phase Arrow:</strong> Empower an arrow to pass through physical barriers. <strong>Hail of Arrows: </strong>split it into many arrows that covers an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Archer III]{Arcane Archer III}</td>\n<td>H, AA II</td>\n<td><strong>Imbue:</strong> an arrow with an area of effect power once per turn. <strong>Death Arrow:</strong> fired once per day (victim who is Shaken or Wounded must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll or die).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Trickster]{Arcane Trickster}</td>\n<td>S, AB or MP, Sneak Attack, Thievery d8</td>\n<td><strong>Ranged Legerdemain:</strong> Can use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} at Range of 5\" at –2 penalty. <strong>Impromptu Attack:</strong> Once per encounter, trickster may use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sneak Attack]{Sneak Attack} without @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Trickster II]{Arcane Trickster II}</td>\n<td>S, AT</td>\n<td><strong>Invisible Thief:</strong> Once per day, automatically cast invisibility for 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} and an automatic raise (no roll).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Trickster III]{Arcane Trickster III}</td>\n<td>V, AT II</td>\n<td><strong>Surprise Spells:</strong> The hero's spells benefit from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sneak Attack]{Sneak Attack}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Assassin]{Assassin}</td>\n<td>S, Sneak Attack</td>\n<td><strong>Hide in Plain Sight:</strong> –4 to be seen if assassin doesn't move. <strong>Resistance to Poison:</strong> +4 to resist @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{Poison}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Assassin II]{Assassin II}</td>\n<td>V, Assassin</td>\n<td><strong>Infiltration Expertise:</strong> The assassin can spend seven days creating an unfailing identity for herself. <strong>Swift Death:</strong> Once per day, the killer gains @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} on a foe of her choice.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Assassin III]{Assassin III}</td>\n<td>H, Assassin II</td>\n<td><strong>Death Attack:</strong> If assassin attacks with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} and causes at least one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}, the victim must make @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll or die.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dragon Disciple]{Dragon Disciple}</td>\n<td>S, AB or MP, Arcana d6</td>\n<td><strong>Breath Attack:</strong> 3d6 damage plus @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trapping} effects, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Cone Template}, once per encounter.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dragon Disciple II]{Dragon Disciple II}</td>\n<td>V, DD</td>\n<td><strong>Wings:</strong> The character grows wings for @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Flight]{Flight} (Pace 8).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dragon Disciple III]{Dragon Disciple III}</td>\n<td>H, DD II</td>\n<td><strong>Dragon Form:</strong> Twice per day the dragon disciple may take the form of a dragon of her bloodline.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Duelist]{Duelist}</td>\n<td>S, Ag d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td><strong>Surgical Strike:</strong> +2 damage with certain weapons. <strong>Parry:</strong> Duelist may Defend if she hasn't acted yet for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} bonus +6.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Duelist II]{Duelist II}</td>\n<td>S, Deulist</td>\n<td><strong>Crippling Strike:</strong> Reduce foe's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} by 2 until healed.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Duelist III]{Duelist III}</td>\n<td>V, Duelist II</td>\n<td><strong>Deflect Arrows:</strong> –2 to be hit with physical ranged attacks.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Knight]{Eldritch Knight}</td>\n<td>S, AB or MP, Fighting d8</td>\n<td><strong>Eldritch Recharge:</strong> Regain a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} with raise on an attack or arcane skill.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Knight II]{Eldritch Knight II}</td>\n<td>V, EK</td>\n<td><strong>Eldritch Strike:</strong> to add +2 to the attack total. Spend 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} after making an attack to add +2 to the attack total.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Eldritch Knight III]{Eldritch Knight III}</td>\n<td>H, EK II</td>\n<td><strong>Imp. Eldritch Strike:</strong> Spend 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} after making a successful attack to increase the attack's damage by +2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extreme Explorer]{Extreme Explorer}</td>\n<td>S, Survival d6, See text</td>\n<td><strong>Pathfinding:</strong> Increase travel speed by 10%, possibly avoid Enemy encounters.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extreme Explorer II]{Extreme Explorer II}</td>\n<td>V, EE</td>\n<td><strong>Epic Tales:</strong> Tell a tale to grant the party a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} while resting.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extreme Explorer III]{Extreme Explorer III}</td>\n<td>H, EE II</td>\n<td><strong>Call Down the Legends:</strong> Summon 5 Shades of heroes for one hour.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Loremaster]{Loremaster}</td>\n<td>S, Sm d8, See text</td>\n<td><strong>Lore:</strong> Free reroll on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Cosmology]{Cosmology}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Religion]{Religion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Loremaster II]{Loremaster II}</td>\n<td>V, LM</td>\n<td><strong>Secret:</strong> Gain an ability from any core Class Edge.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Loremaster III]{Loremaster III}</td>\n<td>H, LM II</td>\n<td><strong>Greater Lore:</strong> Gain any 2 new powers available in the campaign.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"main-class\">\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Theurge]{Mystic Theurge}</td>\n<td>S, ABs, See text</td>\n<td><strong>Combined Spells: </strong>Cast two spells at once, rolling an arcane skill for each along with the Wild Die.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Theurge II]{Mystic Theurge II}</td>\n<td>V, MT</td>\n<td><strong>Spell Synergy: </strong>Reduce cost of each spell when using Combined Spells ability.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mystic Theurge III]{Mystic Theurge III}</td>\n<td>H, MT II</td>\n<td><strong>Spell Synthesis: </strong>When the theurge uses her Combined Spells ability she reduces the cost of each spell by one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} (to a minimum of 1).</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Racial Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Adamantine Body]{Adamantine Body}</td>\n<td>N, Warforged</td>\n<td>Start with +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bladedancer]{Bladedancer}</td>\n<td>N, Elf, A d8, Fighting d8, Two-Weapon Fighting</td>\n<td>Make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{run} roll, and get a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack at everything in his path.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extra Shifter Ability]{Extra Shifter Ability}</td>\n<td>N, Shifter</td>\n<td>Gains one additional shifting ability.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Healing Factor]{Healing Factor}</td>\n<td>N, Shifter, V d8</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak roll} on any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} when ending shifting.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Overload Metabolism]{Overload Metaolism}</td>\n<td>N, Warforged, A d8, Str d8</td>\n<td>Once per session make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll to repair one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}. two on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Reduce @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} one die type for 10 minutes.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Primal Fury]{Primal Fury}</td>\n<td>S, Half-orc or Orc, Berserk</td>\n<td>No penalty to end rage, and the hero will not hit an ally on a Critical Failure with her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Psicrystal]{Psicyrstal}</td>\n<td>N, Kalashtar, SB (Psionics), Sm d8</td>\n<td>Allows the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Kalashtar]{Kalashtar} to have a fragment of thier personality placed into a srystalline construct with some abilities.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Psiforged Body]{Psiforged Body}</td>\n<td>N, Warforged, AB (Psionics)</td>\n<td>This adds 5 Powers Points for a Psionic Warforged.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Reactive Shifting]{Reactive Shifting}</td>\n<td>N, Shifter, Quick</td>\n<td>Shifters can shift as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} even when not on their turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Running Throw]{Running Throw}</td>\n<td>S, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Str d8, Athletics d8</td>\n<td>The hero moves at least half their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} and throws a weapon may increase their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{range} by 2/4/8.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Scamper]{Scamper}</td>\n<td>S, Halfling, A d8</td>\n<td>Opponents larger than the hero subtract 1 from their attack rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Scamper]{Improved Scamper}</td>\n<td>V, Scamper</td>\n<td>Opponents get no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{gang up} on the hero.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Shieldwall]{Shieldwall}</td>\n<td>S, Hobogoblin, Block</td>\n<td>The hero can add his shield modifier to an adjacent ally.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Shifter Stamina]{Shifter Stamina}</td>\n<td>N, Shifter</td>\n<td>The adventurer is immune to nonlethal damage and the effects of fatigue while they are shifted.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sunder]{Sunder}</td>\n<td>S, Dwarf</td>\n<td>The adventurer ignores 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{armor}, or 2 points on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} of the attack roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Sunder]{Improved Sunder}</td>\n<td>V, Sunder</td>\n<td>The hero ignores 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{armor}, or 4 points on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} of the attack roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.War Cry]{War Cry}</td>\n<td>S, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Intimidation d8</td>\n<td>Once per turn, affect all foes in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template} with an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</figure>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_intbwo9s2if","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":20}}}
{"_id":"dunAw0B1Slwf1514","name":"Bugbear","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Bugbear</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>The goblinoid species—goblins, hobgoblins, and bugbears—were once the dominant civilization in Khorvaire, with the goblinoid Empire of Dhakaan ruling the continent for thousands ofyears. It was crippled by a long conflict with the daelkyr and their aberrant armies; even though the daelkyr were defeated, the seeds of madness took root in the empire and tore it apart. Today there are four primary goblinoid cultures in Khorvaire.</p>\n<p>Known as <em>guul'dar</em>, or \"strong people\", among the <em>dar</em> or goblin races. <em>Guul'dar</em> are born for battle and mayhem being fierce and aggressive. Surviving by raiding and hunting, they bully the weak and despite being bossed around. In Darguun they living in tribes in the Marguul mountains, or in the <em>ghaal'dur </em>tribes ruling Darguun often serving as shock troops being ruled by the hobgoblins with superior numbers and intellect.</p>\n<h3>The Marguul</h3>\n<p>The Marguul bugbears threw off the yoke of the <em>ghaal'dar</em> long ago, seizing territory in the Seawall Mountains in the south of Darguun. They are infamous raiders, and while they have brokered a truce with the Ghaal'dar, anyone venturing into the Seawall Mountains had best travel with a Marguul guide.</p>\n<p>As a Marguul bugbear, you are savage and proud of it. The Marguul worship the Mockery and believe in victory by any means necessary: there is no such thing as honor on the battlefield. It's certainly an unusual choice for a player character, but if you've taken a liking to a particular group of the small folk, you could be a powerful ally.</p>\n<h3>The Heirs of Dhakaan</h3>\n<p>Though the Dhakaani Empire defeated the alien daelkyr, the war left seeds ofcorruption strewn throughout the empire. As Dhakaan began to fall, a number of generals and governors gathered their forces and retreated into shelters deep within the earth, determined to preserve their civilization until the Empire could finally be restored. After thousands of years, their descendants have finally emerged, competing among themselves to determine which leader deserves the imperial crown. Once this is settled, they will turn to the conquest of Darguun and Khorvaire.</p>\n<p>The Dhakaani are far fewer in number than the <em>ghaal'dar</em>; they had to carefully limit their population in the underground vaults they've dwelled in for the past age. However, they have held onto the martial discipline and techniques that allowed their ancestors to dominate the continent. Their weaponsmiths are superior even to the artificers of House Cannith, and they are experts in the working of adamantine and other exotic metals. Anyone who presumes to look down upon goblinoids should be surprised by the skills of the Dhakaani.</p>\n<p>The Heirs of Dhakaan are an agnostic society and don't have clerics, paladins, or druids. Their focus is on martial excellence, and their spiritual leaders are bards, who tell tales of past glory. Among the Dhakaan, goblinoids work together. Hobgoblins are the strategists and commanders, typically having the skills of fighters, bards, or rangers. Bugbears cultivate a focused battle rage and are typically barbarians. Goblins are largely artisans and laborers, but exceptional goblins join the khesh'dar (\"silent folk\"), learning the skills of rogues, monks, or rangers. The khesh'dar spread agents across the Five Nations, and one can never know when a city goblin might turn out to be an assassin.</p>\n<p>As an adventurer from a Dhakaani clan, consider why are you working with the other player characters? Are you a scout gathering information? Are you searching for allies to defeat a rival clan, or to support your own unlikely bid for the Imperial throne? Are you an exile? If so, do you hope to regain your position, or have you abandoned your ties to the Dhakaani?</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Bloodthirsty]{Bloodthirsty}:</strong> Bugbears are very brutal killers and like to inflict pain. </li>\n<li><strong>Brute Strength:</strong> Bugbears are naturally strong, and start with a d6 in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of a d4. This increases their maximum @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} to d12+1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}:</strong> Bugbear eyes are accustomed to the dark of Khyber. Darkvision ignores up to –4 penalties for all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} up to 10\" away. Beyond 10\" they ignore up to –2 penalties. Such vision is in black and white (monchrome) only.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Language}:</strong> Bugbears start with a d8 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Goblin} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Common}.</li>\n<li><strong>Large Size: </strong>Bugbears average about seven to eight feet tall, increasing their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (and therefore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}) by 1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Long-limbs]{Long-limbs}:</strong> Bugbears are long-limbed goblinoids. They have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1. </li>\n<li><strong>Silent Ambushers:</strong> Bugbears are natural ambushers. They start with a d6 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth}. This increases their maximum @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} to a d12+1.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/bugbear.webp\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/races/bugbear.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L4NqGfd9AVja33DY"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":3},"cf":{"id":"temp_di56kj2145l","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}}}
