{"_id":"e14FyGL3uSJw5CmD","name":"Rogue","content":"<p>Rogues devote as much effort to mastering the use of a variety of skills as they do to perfecting their combat abilities, giving them a broad expertise that few other characters can match. Many rogues focus on stealth and deception, while others refine the skills that help them in a dungeon environment, such as climbing, finding and disarming traps, and opening locks.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Athletics, Gambling, Notice, Stealth, Taunt, Thievery</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Alertness, Fleet-Footed, Luck Great Luck</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Close Fighting, Improved Close Fighting, Dirty Fighter, Really Dirty Fighter, Dodge, Improved Dodge, Feint, Free Runner, Level Headed, Improved Level Headed, Steal Away</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Acrobats, Combat Acrobat. Escape Artist, Femme Fatale/Ladykiller, Thief</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Connections, Humiliate, Streetwise</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.FZK94Vor67GYJ8FI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"eJfdGORlbXxo3sH6","name":"Knight","content":"<p>You belong to an order of knights who have sworn oaths to achieve a certain goal. The nature of this goal depends on the order you serve, but in your eyes it is without question a vital and honorable endeavor. Most of these orders aren't limited to fighting types, but are open to all sorts of folk who are willing to battle and die for the order's cause. Particularly with the prevalence of magic there are some knightly orders that look for battlemages, such as the Knights Arcane of Aundair.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Athletics, Battle, Fighting, Riding, Traditions</p>\n<p><strong>Hindrance:</strong> Code of Honor</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Brave</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Fast Mount, Mounted Combatant, Steady Hands, Trademark Weapon, Improved Trademark Weapon</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Command, Command Presence, Fervor, Fantaticism, Hold the Line!, Death before Dishonor, Natural Leader, Tactician, Master Tactician</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Knight, Monster Hunter</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Bolster, Strong Willed, Iron Will</p>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.m7XwStWRKJSYManh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"exRQR7Zhpttzk1cD","name":"Cleric","content":"<p>It’s important to understand that in Eberron, not all priests can wield divine energies. A priest provides spiritual guidance to a community and congregation and they don’t need magic to do this. A cleric is a full-fledged divine champion, and someone who possesses such a powerful connection wouldn’t waste that power on sermons and everyday services. People of faith assume that such power has a purpose.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Faith, Fighting, Healing, Religion</p>\n<p><strong>Hindrance: </strong>Chain of Command, Vow</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Arcane Background (Miracles), Attractive, Charismatic</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Any combat edge for a warrior cleric</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Command, Fantaticism, Inspire</p>\n<p><strong>Power Edges:</strong> Holy/Unholy Warrior</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Holy Adept</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Strong Willed, Iron Will, Work the Room</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Champion</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.z8YQ22r7SzqkZWpt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"ey93l8xiuHBUSEz7","name":"Navigation","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Navigation</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Traveling the treacherous seas of Eberron is an adventure in itself. The following quick method helps you determine how quickly a vessel travels and whether or not it stays on course.</p>\n<p>Each hex on the map is equal to 10 miles (3 leagues). Vessels cross as many squares as their Travel Speed each day, modified by their crew.</p>\n<p>The captain must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} roll for each day of travel and add the modifiers listed below:</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\" style=\"width:50%\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Navigation Modifiers</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Mod</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Circumstance</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>Vessel stays along coast</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>–2</td>\n<td>The captain has no compass</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>–2</td>\n<td>Most of the crew has no @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} skill</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>–1</td>\n<td>Crew has an average @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} skill of d4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>Crew has an average @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} skill of d6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>Crew has an average @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} skill of d8</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>Crew has an average @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} skill of d10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>Crew has an average @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} skill of d12</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>With a success, the vessel moves as expected. A raise adds +1 to the vessel’s movement. Failure means the ship travels its expected movement in a random direction—roll a [[/r d6]] to determine the direction of the hex it moves to.</p>\n<p>If the roll moves the vessel into a land mass on the map, it may run aground. The captain must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} roll (the crew adds a group support roll as well to account for lookouts in the crow’s nest and so forth).</p>\n<p>A raise means the ship avoids the shoals, sandbars, or reefs and suffers no ill effects. Success means the ship is beached. It takes [[/r 2d20]] hours to pull it free, or [[/r 1d20]] hours if another ship is available. Failure indicates the ship has run aground. The vessel is wrecked and everyone aboard must swim to land or drown.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-links-title\">Ship Setting Rules</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor and Swimming]{Armor and Swimming}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cabin Fever]{Cabin Fever}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Careening]{Careening}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Pay]{Crew Pay}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Provisions]{Crew Provisions}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fighting Below Deck]{Fighting Below Deck}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{Nautical Contact}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Navigation]{Navigation}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Fire]{Ship Fire}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Repairs]{Ship Repairs}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Storms at Sea]{Storms at Sea}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1},"cf":{"id":"temp_500ev3usjom","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Nautical Campaigns","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"fbHDxYw5uRcdeUph","name":"Assassin","content":"<p>A member of House Phiarlan, House Thuranni’s Shadow Network, the Black Dogs of House Ghallanda, or an agent of one of the Five Nations of Galifar such as a Dark Lantern, assassins pose a threat but only to their targets. House Tarkanan is known to have assassins among its ranks as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Athletics, Fighting, Intimidation, Notice, Shooting, Stealth, Thievery</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Alertness, Fleet-Footed, Quick</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Calculating, Close Fighting, Improved Close Fighting, Dirty Fighter, Really Dirty FIghter, Dodge, Improved Dodge, Extraction, Improved Extraction, Feint, First Strike, Improved First Strike, Free Runner, Killer Instinct, Marksman</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Acrobat, Combat Acrobat, Assassin, Escape Artist, Thief</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Connections, Streetwise</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges: </strong>Danger Sense</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.pbfHHDOqLV1c2mv8"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pkglbsbzxv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"fggYxuKdsRgZf1sw","name":"Armor Table","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table gear-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Armor</h2>\n<div class=\"table-summary\">\n<p>Armor is written in parentheses next to a character’s Toughness, like this: 11 (2). This means 2 points of the character’s 11 Toughness comes from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}. An @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{Armor Piercing} attack can bypass those 2 points but not the other 9.</p>\n<p>Note that greaves (leg guards) and vambraces (arm guards) are listed as pairs. Halve the weight and cost if a character wears only half the set (Minimum Strength doesn’t change).</p>\n</div>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" style=\"width:35%\" scope=\"col\">Item</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" style=\"width:15%\" scope=\"col\">Armor</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" style=\"width:15%\" scope=\"col\">Min Str.</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" style=\"width:15%\" scope=\"col\">Weight</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" style=\"width:20%\" scope=\"col\">Cost</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"table-column-header table-subheader-center\" colspan=\"5\" scope=\"colgroup\"><span class=\"table-subheader-center-wrapper\"> <span class=\"table-subheader-center-content\">Cloth/Hide Leather</span> </span> <span class=\"table-body-description\">Heavy winter clothing, supple leather armor, soft hides.</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Hide Jacket]{Hide Jacket} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>5 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Hide Leggings]{Hide Leggings} (legs)</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Leather Armor]{Leather Armor} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>5 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Leather Pants]{Leather Pants} (legs)</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Leather Skullcap]{Leather Skullcap} (head)</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Quilted Armor]{Quilted Armor} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>5 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Robes]{Robes} (torso, arms, legs)</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>2 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Thick Hides]{Thick Hides} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>7</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"table-column-header table-subheader-center\" colspan=\"5\" scope=\"colgroup\"><span class=\"table-subheader-center-wrapper table-subheader-center-content\">Light Armor</span> <span class=\"table-body-description\">Thick leather, boiled leather, cuir bouilli, tough hides.</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Armored Robes]{Armored Robes} (Torso, arms, legs)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[world.savage-eberron-equipment.Chain Shirt]{Chain Shirt} (torso)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>25 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Chitin Armor]{Chitin Armor} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>40 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Darkleaf Breastplate]{Darkleaf Breastplate} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>1,500 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Heavy Hide Jacket]{Heavy Hide Jacket} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>20 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Heavy Hide Leggings]{Heavy Hide Leggings} (legs)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>7</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[world.savage-eberron-equipment.Lamellar Cuirass (Leather)]{Lamellar Cuirass (Leather)} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>35 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[world.savage-eberron-equipment.Lamellar Greaves (Leather)]{Lamellar Greaves (Leather)} (legs)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Leafweave Breastplate]{Leafweave Breastplate} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>500 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Leather Greaves]{Leather Greaves} (legs)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Leather Helmet]{Leather Helmet} (head)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>4 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Studded Leather]{Studded Leather} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>40 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"table-column-header table-subheader-center\" colspan=\"5\" scope=\"colgroup\"><span class=\"table-subheader-center-wrapper table-subheader-center-content\">Medium Armor</span> <span class=\"table-body-description\">Chain, splint, metal scale, steel lamellar.</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Banded Armor]{Banded Armor} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>25</td>\n<td>75 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Banded Greaves]{Banded Greaves} (legs)</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>30 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Chain Mail Coif or Helm]{Chain Mail Coif or Helm} (head)</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>10 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Chain Mail Hauberk]{Chain Mail Hauberk} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>25</td>\n<td>75 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Chain Mail Leggings]{Chain Mail Leggings} (legs)</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>30 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Darkleaf Banded Mail]{Darkleaf Banded Mail} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>2,500 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Lamellar Cuirass (Steel)]{Lamellar Cuirass (Steel)} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>25</td>\n<td>85 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Lamellar Greaves (Steel)]{Lamellar Greaves (Steel)} (legs)</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>35 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Plate Helm (Pot)]{Plate Helm (Pot)} (head)</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>100 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Scale Mail]{Scale Mail} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>25</td>\n<td>75 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Scorpion Breastplate]{Scorpion Breastplate} (torso, arms, head)</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>20</td>\n<td>300 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Splint Mail]{Splint Mail} (torso, arms)</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>25</td>\n<td>75 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"table-column-header table-subheader-center\" colspan=\"5\" scope=\"colgroup\"><span class=\"table-subheader-center-wrapper table-subheader-center-content\">Heavy Armor</span> <span class=\"table-body-description\">Heavy steel armor made with “plates” of metal or similiar material.</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Plate Armor]{Plate Armor} (torso)</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>30</td>\n<td>750 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Plate Greaves]{Plate Greaves} (legs)</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>20</td>\n<td>300 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Plate Helm (Enclosed)]{Plate Helm (Enclosed)} (head)</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>150 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"5\"><strong><em>Notes:</em></strong> -1 to vision-based @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"striped-row-offset\">\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Plate Vambraces]{Plate Vambraces} (arms)</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>15</td>\n<td>300 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.War Chitin]{War Chitin} (torso, arms, legs, head)</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>40</td>\n<td>1,500 gp</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"swadetest","system":"swade","coreVersion":"0.7.8","systemVersion":"0.15.0"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ib2qus6sn1","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/2.1. Gear Tables","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":2}}}
