{"_id":"kEuyhP3uXRABm8HM","name":"Crew Provisions","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Crew Provisions</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>The crews of ships must eat and drink, and ensuring each vessel is properly provisioned is a major concern of any captain.</p>\n<p>To keep things simple, provisions are purchased as generic “points” rather than tracking every bit of food and water required. Each point represents one day’s food, water, and other supplies for each man on board, and costs 5 silver sovereigns per head. This includes fruit capable of staving off scurvy.</p>\n<p>Every 500 points of provisions takes up one cargo space.</p>\n<p>Note that provisions are not the same as “Food” that can be bought and sold at ports. Provisions are biscuits, hardtack, and water. Food is fruit, bread, grain, wine, and other “luxuries.” A cargo space worth of Food can be converted into 50 provisions in an emergency.</p>\n<h2 class=\"blue-example\">Example:</h2>\n<p><em>The Frigate Jolly Edward sets sail with twelve crew. The captain expects to be at sea for at least a month, so he needs 12 provisions for each of 30 days, or 360 provisions. He decides to play it safe and buys 500 provisions. The provisions cost 500 pieces of eight and take up one cargo space.</em></p>\n<p><em>If the ship runs out of food, the captain could convert a cargo space worth of “Food” (a commodity) to 50 provisions. This would feed his 12-man crew for about 4 days.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Hunger:</strong> Wild Cards suffer from starvation normally (one provision a day counts as adequate food). For the rest of the crew, make a group Vigor roll each day they have half rations (one provision for every two men). Subtract 2 if the men have less than this.</p>\n<p>Should the crew collectively reach Incapacitated state, 10% of the men perish each day from starvation. Most crews mutiny long before this starts to happen.</p>\n<h2 class=\"toc-links-title\">Ship Setting Rules</h2>\n<div class=\"toc-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor and Swimming]{Armor and Swimming}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cabin Fever]{Cabin Fever}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Careening]{Careening}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Pay]{Crew Pay}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crew Provisions]{Crew Provisions}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fighting Below Deck]{Fighting Below Deck}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{Nautical Contact}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Navigation]{Navigation}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Fire]{Ship Fire}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Ship Repairs]{Ship Repairs}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Storms at Sea]{Storms at Sea}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_500ev3usjom","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Nautical Campaigns","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"kIpE7V9cwUa2USNX","name":"Returning","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<h3>Thrown Weapon Enchantment</h3>\n<p>The weapon returns to its user’s hand at the end of her turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Enchantment Points:</strong> 1</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 3,000 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> —</p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_d6wak2736pv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/6.1. Enchantments","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"kSWcoQ4cWv2MO60t","name":"Edges","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Edges</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Below is a list of Edges common to most settings. You’ll find new Edges designed for your game world in official <em>Savage Worlds</em> books as well.</p>\n<p>The Edges are grouped by type to help during character creation. You’ll find a summary below.</p>\n<p>Unless an Edge specifically says otherwise, it may only be selected once.</p>\n<p>The core base Edges are those presented in <em>Pathfinder for Savage Worlds</em> rather than the <em>Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</em>.</p>\n<div>\n<div>\n<h3>Requirements</h3>\n<p>Below each Edge is the minimum Rank (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Advancement}) required to take it along with any other prerequisites such as attributes, skills, or other Edges.</p>\n</div>\n<h2>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Setting Edges}</h2>\n<p>To keep this Edge summary list managable @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Setting Edges} for <span style=\"color:#e03e2d\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Classes}</span>, <span style=\"color:#e03e2d\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Dragonmarks}</span>, <span style=\"color:#e03e2d\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Prestige edges}</span>, and <span style=\"color:#e03e2d\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Edges]{Racial edges}</span> have been moved to a seperate page.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<figure class=\"figure table-figure\">\n<figcaption class=\"figure-heading\">Edge Summaries</figcaption>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Background Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Alertness]{Alertness}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} Rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ambidextrous]{Ambidextrous}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>Ignore –2 penalty when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} rolls with off-hand.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)]{Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for outcasts that manifest an Aberrant Dragonmark.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Divine Magic)]{Arcane Background (Divine Magic)}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for the faithful who follow one of the religions of Eberron.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Magic)]{Arcane Background (Magic)}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for wizards that study and manipulate the fabric of magic.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Psionics)]{Arcane Background (Psionics)}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for those that use their own mental energy to manipulate matter and people. Most common in Sarlona.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Arcane skills targeting the hero suffer a −2 penalty (even if cast by allies!); magical damage is reduced by 2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Arcane Resistance]{Improved Arcane Resistance}</td>\n<td>N, Arcane Resistance</td>\n<td>As Arcane Resistance except penalty is increased to −4 and magical damage is reduced by 4.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Aristocrat]{Aristocrat}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with upper class.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Attractive]{Attractive}</td>\n<td>N, V d6</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Very Attractive]{Very Attractive}</td>\n<td>N, Attractive</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Berserk]{Berserk}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>After being @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken or Wounded}, melee attacks must be@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Attack]{Wild Attacks}, +1 die type to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}, +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}, ignore one level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll hits random target. Take @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} after every five consecutive rounds, may choose to end rage with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll –2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brave]{Brave}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks and –2 to rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brawny]{Brawny}</td>\n<td>N, St d6, V d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (and therefore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}) +1. Treat @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Strength} as one die type higher for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Gear Notes]{Encumbrance} and Minimum Strength to use weapons, armor, or equipment.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute}</td>\n<td>N. St d6, V d6</td>\n<td>Link @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Agility} (including resistance). Short @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} of any thrown item increased by +1. Double that for the adjusted Medium Range, and double again for Long Range.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Charismatic]{Charismatic}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll when using @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Elan]{Elan}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>+2 when spending a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to reroll a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fame]{Fame}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>+1 Persuasion rolls when recognized (Common Knowledge), double usual fee for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Famous]{Famous}</td>\n<td>S, Fame</td>\n<td>+2  @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} when recognized, 5× or more usual fee for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fast Healer]{Fast Healer}</td>\n<td>N, Vd8</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Vigor} when rolling for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{natural healing}; check every 3 days.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fleet-Footed]{Fleet-Footed}</td>\n<td>N, A d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} +2, increase running die one step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.House Scion]{House Scion}</td>\n<td>N, DGMK Race</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with your Dragonmarked House.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Natural Swimmer]{Natural Swimmer}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} to swimming, +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} when swimming, and can hold breath 50% longer.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Linguist]{Linguist}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d6</td>\n<td>Character has d6 in languages equal to half her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Smarts} die.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Luck]{Luck}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>+1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} at the start of each session.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Great Luck]{Great Luck}</td>\n<td>N, Luck</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} at the start of each session.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Quick]{Quick}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>The hero may discard and redraw @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} of 5 or lower.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Character starts with three times the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{starting funds} and an annual salary.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Filthy Rich]{Filthy Rich}</td>\n<td>N, Rich</td>\n<td>Five times @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{starting funds} and an annual salary.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.University Trained]</td>\n<td>N, Sm d8</td>\n<td>\n<p>4 points for Knowledge skills, +1 point for use in a language.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Combat Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Blind Fighting]{Blind Fighting}</td>\n<td>S, A d8, Notice d8</td>\n<td>Hhe hero halves @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Block]{Block}</td>\n<td>S, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>+1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry}, ignore 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up} bonus.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Block]{Improved Block}</td>\n<td>V, Block</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry}, ignore 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up} bonus.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bodyguard]{Bodyguard}</td>\n<td>H, A d8, Block, Notice d8</td>\n<td>Attacks against one adjacent ally are rolled against the heroes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry}, as long as they reamin adjacent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brawler]{Brawler}</td>\n<td>N, St d8, V d8</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} +1, add d4 to damage from fists; or increase it a die type if combined with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws}, or similar abilities.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bruiser]{Bruiser}</td>\n<td>S, Brawler</td>\n<td>Increase unarmed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} damage a die type and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} another +1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brutal]{Brutal}</td>\n<td>N, WC</td>\n<td>+1 to damage for each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Calculating]{Calculating}</td>\n<td>N, St d8, V d8</td>\n<td>Ignore up to 2 points of penalties on one action with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card)} of Five or less.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Close Fighting]{Close Fighting}</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>The hero gains a bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} equal to the enemy's weapon @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Close Fighting]{Improved Close Fighting}</td>\n<td>N, Close Fighting</td>\n<td>As Close Fighting, but also gaining a +1 bonus to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} equal to enemy weapons @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Combat Reflexes]{Combat Reflexes}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} to recover from being @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Counterattack]{Counterattack}</td>\n<td>S, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against one foe per round who failed a  roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Counterattack]{Improved Counterattack}</td>\n<td>V, Counterattack</td>\n<td>As Counterattack, but against three failed attacks per round.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dead Shot]{Dead Shot}</td>\n<td>WC, N, Athletics or Shooting d8</td>\n<td>First successful@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Thorwing) or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll, double damage from when dealt a Joker.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Dodge]{Dodge}</td>\n<td>S, A d8</td>\n<td>−2 to be hit by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{ranged attacks}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Dodge]{Improved Dodge}</td>\n<td>S, Dodge</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} totals.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extraction]{Extraction}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>One adjacent foe doesn’t get a free attack when you @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{withdraw from close combat}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Extraction]{Improved Extraction}</td>\n<td>S, Extraction</td>\n<td>Three adjacent foes don’t get free attacks when you @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{withdraw from close combat.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fast Mount]{Fast Mount}</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Riding d6</td>\n<td>Mount and dismount as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Feint]{Feint}</td>\n<td>N, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>You may choose to make foe resist with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts Instead of Agility} during a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Fighting Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.First Strike]{First Strike}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack once per round when foe moves within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved First Strike]{Improved First Strike}</td>\n<td>H, First Strike</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against up to three foes when they move within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Formation Fighter]{Formation Fighter}</td>\n<td>N, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>Increase @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up} by an additional +1 (Max. still +4).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Free Runner]{Free Runner}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>Ignore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Difficult Ground} and add +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} in foot @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{chases} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (climbing).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy}</td>\n<td>S, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>Roll a second @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die with one melee attack per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Frenzy]{Improved Frenzy}</td>\n<td>V, Frenzy</td>\n<td>Roll a second @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die with up to two melee attacks per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Giant Killer]{Giant Killer}</td>\n<td>V</td>\n<td>+1d6 damage vs. creatures three @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Sizes} larger or more.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Giant Killer]{Improved Giant Killer}</td>\n<td>H, Giant Killer</td>\n<td>Ignore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{armor} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{size} of a creature three @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size and Scale} larger or more.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ground Fighter]{Ground Fighter}</td>\n<td>N, A or St d6</td>\n<td>No penalties when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}. +1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} against a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone} opponent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Hard To Kill]{Hard To Kill}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Ignore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties} when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls to avoid @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Bleeding Out}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Harder To Kill]{Harder To Kill}</td>\n<td>V, Hard to Kill</td>\n<td>Roll a die if the character perishes. Even if he’s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated}, he survives somehow.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improvisational Fighter]{Improvisational Fighter}</td>\n<td>S, Sm d6</td>\n<td>Ignore –2 penalty when attacking with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Improvised Weapons]{Improvised Weapons}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Iron Jaw]{Iron Jaw}</td>\n<td>N, V d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak Rolls} and  @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Vigor} rolls to avoid @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{Knockout Blows}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Killer Instinct]{Killer Instinct}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>The hero gets a free reroll in any opposed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} he initiates.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Level Headed]{Level Headed}</td>\n<td>S, Sm d8</td>\n<td>Draw an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} each round in combat and choose which one to use.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Level Headed]{Improved Level Headed}</td>\n<td>S, Level Headed</td>\n<td>Draw two additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} each round in combat and choose which one to use.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Lunge]{Lunge}</td>\n<td>N, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>Gain +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{reach} with the adventurer's weapon.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Marksman]{Marksman}</td>\n<td>S, Athletics or Shooting d8</td>\n<td>Ignore up to 2 points of penalties from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range},@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{Cover}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Called Shots]{Called Shots}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Speed]{Speed}; or add +1 to first @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Throwing) or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll. Character may not move or fire greater than @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF 1}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist}</td>\n<td>N, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Fighting} +1, fists and feet count as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}, add d4 damage die to unarmed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attacks (or increase die a step if you already have it).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Warrior]{Martial Warrior}</td>\n<td>S, Martial Artist</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Fighting} +2, increase damage die type a step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mighty Blow]{Mighty Blow}</td>\n<td>WC, N, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>On first successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll, double damage when dealt a Joker.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mounted Combatant]{Mounted Combatant}</td>\n<td>N, Riding d8</td>\n<td>Ignores two points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} penalties and may spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak roll} for mount. May also make @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} roll to increase pace of mount by 2\".</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nerves of Steel]{Nerves of Steel}</td>\n<td>N, V d8</td>\n<td>Ignore one level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound Penalties} penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Nerves of Steel]{Improved Nerves of Steel}</td>\n<td>N, Nerves of Steel</td>\n<td>Ignore up to two levels of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound Penalties} penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.No Mercy]{No Mercy}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>+2 damage when spending a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to reroll damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Oversized Weapon Master]{Oversized Weapon Master}</td>\n<td>V, St d10, Fighting d10, Size 0</td>\n<td>The character may use a two-handed weapon with one hand.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rapid Reload]{Rapid Reload}</td>\n<td>N, Shooting d6</td>\n<td>Reduce the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reload]{Reload} value of a weapon by 1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rapid Shot]{Rapid Shot}</td>\n<td>S, Shooting d6</td>\n<td>Increase @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF} by 1 for one @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attack per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Rapid Shot]{Improved Rapid Shot}</td>\n<td>V, Rapid Shot</td>\n<td>Increase @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF} by 1 for up to two @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attacks per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Steady Hands]{Steady Hands}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>Ignore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unstable Platform]{Unstable Platform} penalty; reduce running penalty to –1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Steal Away]{Steal Away}</td>\n<td>S, A d8, Stealth d6</td>\n<td>The hero can make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} roll as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} to hide when withdrawing.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sucker Punch]{Sucker Punch}</td>\n<td>S, A d6, Fighting d8,First Strike</td>\n<td>If the hero succeeds on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}, they recieve a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{Free Attack}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sweep]{Sweep}</td>\n<td>N, St d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll at –2 to hit all targets in weapon’s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach}, no more than once per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Sweep]{Improved Sweep}</td>\n<td>V, Sweep</td>\n<td>As above, but ignore the –2 penalty.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trademark Weapon]{Trademark Weapon}</td>\n<td>N, d8 in related skill</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Throwing), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} total with a specific weapon; +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry} while weapon is readied.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Trademark Weapon]{Improved Trademark Weapon}</td>\n<td>S, Trademark Weapon</td>\n<td>The attack and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry} bonus increases to +2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.True Hero]{True Hero}</td>\n<td>H, WC, Iron Jaw</td>\n<td>When the hero would get @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{incapacitated}, they get a free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak roll}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Two-Weapon Fighting]{Two-Weapon Fighting}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>Make one extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll with a second melee weapon in the off-hand at no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalty.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wrestler]{Wrestler}</td>\n<td>N, A or St d6, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>Make make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting] roll rather than @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Grappling}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Crushing} damage is increased to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} + d4.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Takedown Move]{Takedown Move}</td>\n<td>S, Wrestler</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Push]{Push} moves are opposed at a –2 (–4 on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Leadership Edges</h2>\n<h3>(Command Range is 5\" or 10 Yards)</h3>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.A Few Good Men]{A Few Good Men}</td>\n<td>H, Inspire, Sm d8 , Battle d10</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, add one more Token to force calculations.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Board 'Em]{Board 'Em}</td>\n<td>N, Command, Athletics d8</td>\n<td>+4 to group @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls to grapple an enemy vessel.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Born in Battle]{Born in Battle}</td>\n<td>S, Sm d8, Command, Battle d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} rolls, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls concerning military matters.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Command]{Command}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d6</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras'} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned} recovery rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Command Presence]{Command Presence}</td>\n<td>S, Command</td>\n<td>Increase Command Range to 10″ (20 yards)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Coordinated Firepower]{Coordinated Firepower}</td>\n<td>V, Sm d6, Command, Athletics or Shooting d8+</td>\n<td>The hero adds a flat +2 attack bonus for additional ranged attacks for those within command range. Additional bonus damage on raises.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Cry Havoc!]{Cry Havoc!}</td>\n<td>V, Sp d8, Fervor, Battle d10</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the character may declare a charge that will cause his enemy to lose one extra token.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Death before Dishonor]{Death before Dishonor}</td>\n<td>V, Sp d8, Hold the Line, Battle d8</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the hero gains +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} when rolling for Morale.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Drop!]{Drop!}</td>\n<td>S, Command, Notice 