-edges.Woodsman]{Woodsman}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6, Survival d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} in the wilds.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Social Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bolster]{Bolster}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>May remove @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted or Vulnerable} state after a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Common Bond]{Common Bond}</td>\n<td>WC, N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>The hero may freely give her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to others.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Connections]{Connections}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Contacts provide aid or other favors once per session.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Menacing]{Menacing}</td>\n<td>N, See Text</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Provoke]{Provoke}</td>\n<td>N, Intimidation or Persuasion d6</td>\n<td>May “provoke” foes with a raise on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} roll. See text.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rabble-Rouser]{Rabble-Rouser}</td>\n<td>S, Spirit d8</td>\n<td>Once per turn, affect all foes in a Medium Blast Template with an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Reliable]{Reliable}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Retort]{Retort}</td>\n<td>N, Intimidation d6</td>\n<td>A raise when resisting a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} attack makes the foe @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Skullduggery]{Skullduggery}</td>\n<td>N, Deception d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll when making @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Streetwise]{Streetwise}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d6</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and criminal networking.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Strong Willed]{Strong Willed}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>+2 to resist @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts or Spirit}-based @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Iron Will]{Iron Will}</td>\n<td>S, Brave, Strong Willed</td>\n<td>The bonus now applies to resisting and recovery from powers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Work The Room]{Work The Room}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Once per turn, roll a second die when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Supporting} via @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} and apply result to additional ally.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Work the Crowd]{Work the Crowd}</td>\n<td>S, Work the Room</td>\n<td>As above, but up to twice per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Weird Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Beast Bond]{Beast Bond}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>The hero may spend @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} for animals under her control.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Beast Master]{Beast Master}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Animals like your hero and he has a pet of some sort. See text.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Champion]{Champion}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>+2 damage vs. supernaturally evil creatures.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll at +2 to sense ambushes or similar events.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Healer]{Healer}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} rolls, magical or otherwise.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Liquid Courage]{Liquid Courage}</td>\n<td>N, V d8</td>\n<td>Alcohol increases @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} a die type and ignores one level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties}; –1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility, Smarts}, and related skills.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Scavenger]{Scavenger}</td>\n<td>N, Luck</td>\n<td>May find a needed item once per encounter.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Storm Chaser]{Storm Chaser}</td>\n<td>N, Boating or Piloting d8</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} during storms. Recieve extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} during @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Symbiont Mastery]{Symbiont Mastery}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6</td>\n<td>Recieve +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} in battle of wills with sybionts. With symbiont attached, +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak rolls}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wind Sense]{Wind Sense}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d8, Boating or Piloting d8</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} during @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nautical Contact]{Nautical Contact}. Recieve extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} during @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases}.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Legendary Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Followers]{Followers}</td>\n<td>WC, L</td>\n<td>The hero has five followers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Professional]{Professional}</td>\n<td>L, Max Trait</td>\n<td>The character’s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} and its limit increases one step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Expert]{Expert}</td>\n<td>L, Professional in Trait</td>\n<td>The character’s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} and its limit increases one step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master]{Master}</td>\n<td>WC, L, Expert in Trait</td>\n<td>The character’s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Wild Die} is a d10 with a chosen @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sidekick]{Sidekick}</td>\n<td>WC, L</td>\n<td>The character gains a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card} sidekick.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tough As Nails]{Tough As Nails}</td>\n<td>L, V d8</td>\n<td>The hero can take four @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} before being Incapacitated.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tougher Than Nails]{Tougher Than Nails}</td>\n<td>L, Tough as Nails, V d12</td>\n<td>The hero can take five @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} before being Incapacitated.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Weapon Master]{Weapon Master}</td>\n<td>L, Fighting d12</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry} increases by +1 and Fighting bonus damage die is d8.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master of Arms]{Master of Arms}</td>\n<td>L, Weapon Master</td>\n<td>Parry increases another +1 and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{bonus damage} die is d10.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</figure>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_intbwo9s2if","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":16}}}
