{"_id":"kyZD4VX3J6GxNKzg","name":"Deflecting","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<h3>Shield Enchantment</h3>\n<p>Increase the shield’s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} bonus increased by +1.</p>\n<p><strong>Enchantment Points:</strong> 1</p>\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> 4,000 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</em></p>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_d6wak2736pv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic Items#/CF_SEP/6.1. Enchantments","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"lH5snVbbin3fisoy","name":"Arcane Background (Artificer)","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<h2>Arcane Background (Artificer)</h2>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Edge:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Artificer)]{Arcane Background (Artificer)}</li>\n<li><strong>Requirements:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Artificer]{Artificer}</li>\n<li><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts})</li>\n<li><strong>Artifice:</strong> Artificers may take Edges that require @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Weird Science)]{Arcane Background (Weird Science)}.</li>\n<li><strong>Tools: </strong>Artificers must carry their \"tools\" on their person to activate their powers.</li>\n<li><strong>Malfunction: </strong>When an artificer rolls a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} roll, the Dungeon Master rolls on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules-tables.Manfunction Table]{Manfunction Table} to see what happens.</li>\n<li><strong>Starting Powers:</strong> 2</li>\n<li><strong>Power Points:</strong> 15</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Accelerate Healing]{Accelerate Healing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{Blast}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{Blind}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burrow]{Burrow}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{Burst}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{Conjure Item}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Damage Field]{Damage Field}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{Detect/Conceal Arcana}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Drain Power Points]{Drain Power Points}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{Elemental Manipulation}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{Entangle}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Environmental Protection]{Environmental Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{Farsight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fear]{Fear}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fly]{Fly}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Glyph]{Glyph}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Growth/Shrink]{Growth/Shrink}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{Havoc}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{Illusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{Invisibility}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Leaping]{Leaping}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Light/Darkness}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{Locate}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{Lock/Unlock}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Magic Mark]{Magic Mark}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message]{Message}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Object Reading]{Object Reading}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Planar Travel]{Planar Travel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{Puppet}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{Relief}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{Repair}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{Scrying}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Secret Writing]{Secret Writing}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{Sentry}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Sloth/Speed}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{Slumber}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{Sound/Silence}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{Stun}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{Summon Ally}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{Telekinesis}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{Wall Walker}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{Warrior's Gift}</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<h2>Playing an Artificer</h2>\n<p>In Eberron, magic is almost technology. Spellcasters specialize in certain forms of that technology, while artificers tinker with its fundamental workings. Artificers understand magic on a different level from spellcasters, and do not cast spells as wizards and clerics do. They have an amazing facility with magic items and constructs, and in many ways, they keep the magical world of Eberron running.</p>\n<p>Masters of unlocking magic in everyday objects, artificers are supreme inventors. They see magic as a complex system waiting to be decoded and controlled. Artificers use tools to channel arcane power, crafting magical objects. To cast a spell, an artificer could use alchemist's supplies to create a potent elixir, calligrapher's supplies to inscribe a sigil of power on an ally's armor, or tinker's tools to craft a temporary charm. The magic of artificers is tied to their tools and their talents.</p>\n<h3>ARCANE SCIENCE</h3>\n<p>In the world of Eberron, arcane magic has been harnessed as a form of science and deployed throughout society. Artificers reflect this development. Their knowledge of magical devices, and their ability to infuse mundane items with magic, allows Eberron's most miraculous projects to continue.</p>\n<p>During the Last War, artificers were marshaled on a massive scale. Many lives were saved because of the inventions of brave artificers, but countless lives were also lost because of the mass destruction unleashed by their creations.</p>\n<h3>SEEKERS OF NEW LORE</h3>\n<p>Nothing excites an artificer quite like uncovering a new metal or discovering a source of elemental energy. In artificer circles, new inventions and strange discoveries create the most excitement. Artificers who wish to make their mark must innovate, creating something fresh, rather than iterating on familiar designs.</p>\n<p>This drive for novelty pushes artificers to become adventurers. Eberron's main travel routes and populated regions have long since been explored. Thus, artificers seek the frontiers of civilization in hopes of making the next great discovery in arcane research.</p>\n<h2>Casting</h2>\n<p>Artificers craft, invent, and tinker with their inventions. All your powers are produced by inventions that are crafted using various tools. When creating an artificer, pick at least one kind of tool set that the artificer works with; @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Alchemist Supplies]{alchemist supplies} for potions and ungents, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Tinker's Tools]{tinker's tools} for general tinkering, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Warforged Repair Kit]{warforged repair kit} if they work strictly with warforged, or another artisan tool kit that makes sense.</p>\n<p>In general, it's assumed an artificer is constantly working and tinker on their inventions during downtime. Perhaps before bed, in the morning, or during meals. It should be assumed the inventor takes at least an hour a day preparing items that might be used. If the artificer can't perform this tinkering, or does not have their tools, she can't use her powers.</p>\n<h2>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trappings}</h2>\n<p>As an artificer, you use tools when you cast your spells. When describing your spellcasting, think about how you're using a tool to perform the spell effect. If you cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> using @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Alchemist Supplies]{alchemist supplies}, you could be quickly producing a salve. If you cast it using @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Tinker's Tools]{tinker's tools}, you might have a miniature mechanical spider that binds wounds. When you cast <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em> with a poison effect, you could fling foul chemicals or use a wand that spits venom.</p>\n<p>Artificers take pride in their custom inventions, often giving them creative names to differentiate them from other artificers. Such as \"Elenna's Miraculous Healing Ungent\" or \"Mending Spider\". You should make sure to do the same for your powers.</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yqngxv6403a","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.3. Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":3}}}
{"_id":"lI5IPZPThORV5qsg","name":"Cold Iron","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Cold Iron</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Mined from the deepest depths of Khyber, cold iron is the weakness of certain fiends and fey creatures. Weapons forged with cold iron increase @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} by 2 and cost twice as much as normal.</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_ebw221m1i2","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/2.2. Materials and Craftsmanship","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"lQhddkySLVld21Wj","name":"Traps and Haunts","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<h2>Traps and Haunts</h2>\n<p>Traps are mechanical or magical in nature, usually constructed to protect treasures or stop intruders. They range from simple camouflaged pits to poisoned darts and triggered magical burst effects.</p>\n<p>Haunts function like traps, but are specific supernatural phenomena connected to restless shades or other spirits. These areas react violently to the presence of the living, usually triggering some kind of effect when the area is entered or some item of personal import is touched or approached.</p>\n<p>Here's how to read each trap or haunt's description:</p>\n<p><strong>Type: </strong>Mechanical, Magical, Haunt</p>\n<p><strong>Notice Check:</strong> Yes or No, with any modifier to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll to detect the presence of a trap. Success allows the heroes to react before the trap or haunt is triggered.</p>\n<p><strong>Thievery Check:</strong> Yes or No, with any modifiers to the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} die roll needed to succeed in disabling a trap.</p>\n<p><strong>Effects:</strong> How the trap springs or the haunt manifests, their game effects, and whether or not it can reset</p>\n<p><strong>Wounds:</strong> Haunts can be affected by the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> power. When the haunt is healed a number of Wounds equal to the number listed here, it's disabled.</p>\n<p><strong>Reset:</strong> After a certain duration, a haunt (even a disabled one) resets to its original state. The duration is listed in the haunt. This continues until the haunt is destroyed.</p>\n<p><strong>Destroying a Haunt:</strong> To completely destroy a haunt, its source must be destroyed. This is usually listed before the haunt or in the description. This will often involve destroying something, such as a cursed corpse.</p>\n<br />\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h3>Collapsing Floor</h3>\n<p><strong>Type:</strong> Mechanical; <strong>Notice Check: </strong>Yes, at –2;<strong> Thievery Check:</strong> Yes, at –2</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger:</strong> A hinged section of floor is rigged to give way. Any Size 0 or larger creature entering the room triggers a collapse.</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Victims fall 30 feet (3d6 + 3 damage) unless they make an Evasion roll to dive clear.</p>\n</section>\n<br />\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h3>Vengeful Haunt</h3>\n<p><strong>Type:</strong> Haunt (6' radius); <strong>Notice Check: </strong>No (the spirit appears without warning);<strong> </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Trigger:</strong> Proximity; <strong>Wounds:</strong> 1; <strong>Reset:</strong> 1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> The spirit manifests in front of the victim, causing him to make a Fear check when the ghostly image appears.</p>\n</section>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_5qurmfm60sv","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. The Adventure Toolkit#/CF_SEP/Hazards","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-rules.kTqDlMHJo5qAda2v"},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":8},"journal-links":{"references":{}}}}
{"_id":"lZ1rVk9vwOOm0TuH","name":"Hindrances","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Hindrances</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Hindrances are character flaws and physical handicaps that occasionally make life a little tougher for your hero.</p>\n<p>Some Hindrances have actual game effects. Other, more subjective “roleplaying” Hindrances help you understand and roleplay your character. They should occasionally cause her to act in ways that aren’t necessarily smart, efficient, or in the best interests of the party or the overall goal. That’s what roleplaying games are all about, and the GM should reward you with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies] when your Hindrances cause significant trouble.</p>\n<h3>Hindrances Removed in Savage Eberron from Savage Worlds</h3>\n<p>The following Hindances from <em>Savage Worlds</em> are <strong>not </strong>available in <em>Savage Eberron</em>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"red-text\">Doubting Thomas</span></p>\n<h3>Hindrances Added to Savage Eberron</h3>\n<p>The following Hindrances have been added to <em>Savage Eberron</em>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"red-text\">Apprentice/Novice</span>, <span class=\"red-text\">Chain of Command</span>, <span class=\"red-text\">Combat Shock</span>, <span class=\"red-text\">Dependent</span>, <span class=\"red-text\">Deserter</span>, <span class=\"red-text\">Fanatic</span>, <span class=\"red-text\">Heavy Sleeper</span>, <span class=\"red-text\">Inept</span>, <span class=\"red-text\">Lying Eyes</span>, <span class=\"red-text\">Night Terrors</span>, <span class=\"red-text\">Nightmares</span>, <span class=\"red-text\">Trouble Magnet</span></p>\n</div>\n<figure class=\"figure table-figure\">\n<figcaption class=\"figure-heading\">Hindrance Summaries</figcaption>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.All Thumbs]{All Thumbs} (Minor):</span> –2 to use mechanical or electrical devices.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Anemic]{Anemic} (Minor):</span> –2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} when resisting @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Apprentice/Novice]{Apprentice/Novice} (Minor/Major): </span>Cannot start with higher than a d6 in arcane skill, as Major start with one less power from the Arcane Background.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Arrogant]{Arrogant} (Minor):</span> Likes to dominate his opponent, challenge the most powerful foe in combat.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Bad Eyes]{Bad Eyes} (Minor/Major):</span> –1 to all Trait rolls dependent on vision, or –2 as a Major Hindrance. Eyewear negates penalty but have a 50% chance of breaking when the hero suffers trauma.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Bad Luck]{Bad Luck} (Major):</span> The characters starts with one less @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} per session.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Big Mouth]{Big Mouth} (Minor):</span> Unable to keep secrets and constantly gives away private information.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Blind]{Blind} (Major):</span> –6 to all tasks that require vision (but choice of a free Edge to offset).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Bloodthirsty]{Bloodthirsty} (Major):</span> Never takes prisoners.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Can't Swim]{Can't Swim} (Minor):</span> –2 to swimming (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}) rolls; Each inch moved in water costs 3” of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Cautious]{Cautious} (Minor):</span> The character plans extensively and/or is overly careful.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Chain of Command]{Chain of Command} (Minor/Major):</span> You have to follow orders from a superior, as Major you are expendable.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Clueless]{Clueless} (Major):</span> –1 to Common Knowledge and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Clumsy]{Clumsy} (Major):</span> –2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Code of Honor]{Code of Honor} (Major):</span> The character keeps his word and acts like a gentleman.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Combat Shock]{Combat Shock} (Minor/Major):</span> First round of combat make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} check, at –2 for Major Hindrance.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Curious]{Curious} (Major):</span> The character wants to know about everything.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Death Wish]{Death Wish} (Minor):</span> The hero wants to die after or while completing some epic task.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Delusional]{Delusional} (Minor/Major):</span> The individual believes something strange that causes him occasional or frequent trouble.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Dependent]{Dependent} (Minor):</span> The hero has a dependant they must care for.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Deserter]{Deserter} (Minor/Major):</span> The adventurer was a deserter from the Last War.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Driven]{Driven} (Minor/Major):</span> The hero’s actions are driven by some important goal or belief.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Elderly]{Elderly} (Major):</span> –1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace}, running, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility, Strength, and Vigor}. Hero gets 5 extra skill points.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Enemy]{Enemy} (Minor/Major):</span> The character has a recurring nemesis.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Fanatic]{Fanatic} (Major):</span> The hero fanatically believes in his country, monarch, or religion.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Greedy]{Greedy} (Minor/Major):</span> The individual is obsessed with wealth and material possessions.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Habit]{Habit} (Minor/Major):</span> Addicted to something, suffers @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} if deprived.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Hard of Hearing]{Hard of Hearing} (Minor/Major):</span> –4 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} sounds; automatic failure if completely deaf.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Heavy Sleeper]{Heavy Sleeper} (Major):</span> –4 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} to wake up. –4 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} to stay awake.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Heroic]{Heroic} (Major):</span> The character always helps those in need.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Hesitant]{Hesitant} (Minor):</span> Draw two @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} and take the lowest (except Jokers, which may be kept).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Illiterate]{Illiterate} (Minor):</span> The character cannot read or write.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Inept]{Inept} (Minor/Major):</span> Start with 2 fewer skill points, 4 fewer as major.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Impulsive]{Impulsive} (Major):</span> The hero leaps before he looks.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Jealous]{Jealous} (Minor/Major):</span> The individual covets what others have.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Lying Eyes]{Lying Eyes} (Minor):</span> –1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Gambling]{Gambling}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls when lying. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Loyal]{Loyal} (Minor):</span> The hero is loyal to his friends and allies.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Mean]{Mean} (Minor):</span> –1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Mild Mannered]{Mild Mannered} (Minor):</span> –2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Mute]{Mute} (Major):</span> The hero cannot speak.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Nightmares]{Nightmares} (Minor):</span> –1 penalty to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Obese]{Obese} (Minor):</span> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} +1, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} –1 and running die of d4. Treat @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} as one die type lower for Min @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Obligation]{Obligation} (Minor/Major):</span> The character has a weekly obligation of 20 (Minor) to 40 (Major) hours.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.One Arm]{One Arm} (Major):</span> –4 to tasks (such as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}) that require two hands.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.One Eye]{One Eye} (Major):</span> –2 to actions at 5″ (10 yards) or more distance.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Outsider]{Outsider} (Minor/Major):</span> The character doesn’t fit in to the local environment and subtracts 2 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls. As a Major Hindrance she has no legal rights or other serious consequences.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Overconfident]{Overconfident} (Major):</span> The hero believes she can do anything.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Pacifist]{Pacifist} (Minor/Major):</span> Fights only in self-defense as a Minor Hindrance, won’t fight at all as Major.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Phobia]{Phobia} (Minor/Major):</span> The character is afraid of something, and subtracts –1/–2 from all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} rolls in its presence.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Poverty]{Poverty} (Minor):</span> Half starting funds and the character is always broke.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Quirk]{Quirk} (Minor):</span> The individual has some minor but persistent foible that often annoys others.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Ruthless]{Ruthless} (Minor/Major):</span> The character does what it takes to get her way.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Secret]{Secret} (Minor/Major):</span> The hero has a dark secret of some kind.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Shamed]{Shamed} (Minor/Major):</span> The individual is haunted by some tragic event from her past.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Slow]{Slow} (Minor/Major):</span> Pace –1, reduce running die one step. As Major, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} –2, –2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} and rolls to resist @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}. Neither may take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fleet-Footed]{Fleet-Footed} Edge.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Small]{Small} (Minor):</span> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} are reduced by 1. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} cannot be reduced below –1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Stubborn]{Stubborn} (Minor):</span> The character wants his way and rarely admits his mistakes.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Suspicious]{Suspicious} (Minor/Major):</span> The individual is paranoid. As a Major Hindrance, allies subtract 2 when rolling to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} him.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Thin Skinned]{Thin Skinned} (Minor/Major):</span> The character is particularly susceptible to personal attacks. As a Minor Hindrance, he subtracts two when resisting @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} tests. As a Major, he subtracts four.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Tongue-Tied]{Tongue-Tied} (Major):</span> The character often misspeaks or can’t get her words out. –1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Trouble Magnet]{Trouble Magnet} (Minor/Major):</span> The adventurer always seems to attract the worst kind of trouble.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Ugly]{Ugly} (Minor/Major):</span> The character is physically unattractive and subtracts 1 or 2 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Vengeful]{Vengeful} (Minor/Major):</span> The adventurer seeks payback for slights against her. As a Major Hindrance, she’ll cause physical harm to get it.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Vow]{Vow} (Minor/Major):</span> The individual has pledged himself to some cause.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Wanted]{Wanted} (Minor/Major):</span> The character is wanted by the authorities.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Yellow]{Yellow} (Major):</span> –2 to Fear checks and resisting @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class=\"lead-bold\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.Young]{Young} (Minor/Major):</span> Minor has 4 attribute points and 10 skill points, extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} per session. Major has 3 attribute points, 10 skill points, and two extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} per session.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</figure>\n<img class=\"figure table-figure\" src=\"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-savage-eberron/atmosphere/camp.webp\" /></div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_intbwo9s2if","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":3}}}
{"_id":"m5GjQ6rQDecG4uBo","name":"Alchemical Items Table","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table gear-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Alchemical Items</h2>\n<div class=\"table-summary\">\n<p>The following items may be found in most towns with an alchemist's shop.</p>\n</div>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Type</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Range</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Damage</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">AP</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">ROF</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Blast</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Weight</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Cost</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Alchemist's Acid]{Alchemist's Acid}</td>\n<td>3/6/12</td>\n<td>2d4</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{SBT}</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>40 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>Thrown like a grenade. Those within the template take 2d4 damage when hit and 2d4&amp;ndash;2 damage at the start of their next turn unless the acid is washed off somehow.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"striped-row-offset\">\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Alchemist's Acid]{Alchemist's Acid}</td>\n<td>3/6/12</td>\n<td>2d4</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{SBT}</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>A sticky, flammable liquid that ignites on impact. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy Weapon}. Those within the template take 2d4 damage when hit and 2d4&amp;ndash;2 damage at the start of their next turn unless dowsed with water. Target might catch @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fire]{Fire}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"striped-row-offset\">\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Antitoxin]{Antitoxin, vial}</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>.5</td>\n<td>75 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>Grants a +4 bonus to resist @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} for one hour.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"striped-row-offset\">\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Holy Water (flask)]{Holy Water}</td>\n<td>3/6/12</td>\n<td>2d4</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{SBT}</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>25 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>Holy water can be thrown in a flask or splashed on an adjacent creature. Undead and certain evil creatures (DM's call) within the template take 2d4 damage when hit and 2d4–2 damage at the start of their next turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"striped-row-offset\">\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Smokestick]{Smokestick}</td>\n<td>3/6/12</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{MBT}</td>\n<td>.25</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>An alchemically treated stick that creates thick smoke (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dark illumination}) in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} for one minute. Dissipates in strong wind in one round.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"striped-row-offset\">\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Smokestick, Noxious]{Smokestick, Noxious}</td>\n<td>3/6/12</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{MBT}</td>\n<td>.5</td>\n<td>125 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>An alchemically treated stick that creates thick smoke (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dark illumination}) in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} for one minute. Dissipates in strong wind in one round. Those in the cloud must roll a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} check or become @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} from retching and coughing.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"striped-row-offset\">\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Sunrod]{Sunrod}</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>A gold and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Dragonshards]{Eberron dragonshard residum} tipped iron rod that provides normal light in a 30 foot radius for six hours. It increases @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination} one level for another 30' beyond that. It emits no heat, and counts as sunlight.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"striped-row-offset\">\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Tanglefoot bag]{Tanglefoot bag}</td>\n<td>1/2/4</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>50 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>A Size 3 or smaller victim hit by this small sack of sticky materials is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} for five rounds and must make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll or be stuck to the ground (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Entangled}) as well.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"striped-row-offset\">\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Thunderstone]{Thunderstone}</td>\n<td>3/6/12</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{MBT}</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>30 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>An alchemical rock with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Dragonshards]{Eberron dragonshard residum} that explodes with a deafening boom when struck against a hard surface. Anyone a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll or be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} as well as deafened for one hour.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"striped-row-offset\">\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Tindertwig]{Tindertwig}</td>\n<td>3/6/12</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>—</td>\n<td>1 gp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr></tr>\n<tr class=\"table-body-notes\">\n<td colspan=\"8\"><strong><em>Notes: </em></strong>A thin stick that alights with flame when struck against a hard surface. It allows torches and other flammable substances to be lit in a single action.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"striped-row-offset\">\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ib2qus6sn1","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/2. Gear#/CF_SEP/2.1. Gear Tables","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"monks-enhanced-journal":{"_viewcount":1}}}
